text:
i know the intention is well meaning, and i am by no means looking for any apologies. but i am growing tired of hearing, “you’re lucky you didn’t get married. you’re lucky you don’t share a child. you’re lucky you got out as soon as you did.”
.
like most survivors of emotional and psychological abuse, i am sensitive to language. (communication was my abuser’s weapon of choice after all.) and the word, “lucky” just doesn’t sit well with me in this context. there was nothing lucky about what i experienced. could it have been worse? i don’t know. it’s impossible for me to imagine worse.
.
to call me lucky invalidates my trauma. it makes trauma a competition, when it is anything but.
.
to call me lucky also minimizes my strength, my courage, my foresight, my intuition, my resourcefulness, my self respect, and everything else i needed to muster up inside me to get myself out of a heartbreaking situation while i was experiencing “my worst.”
.
so please stop calling me lucky. 🍀 call me a noble, worthy, badass warrior instead. 💛🦋

text:
i look like hell today. for the last 15 years ive had nightmares of an abuser who i know to be dead. sexual assault sucks and the ptsd that comes after is real. i was in emdr therapy but it got too expsensive so i stopped going. the dreams had seemed to have stopped so i didnt think anything of stopping therapy. i was mistaken. the dreams have come back and idk why. my kids are what pushes me through the day. today is already at a rough start itll probably be a rough day but ill make it through because i have to. i didnt want to get out of bed but i made myself. im a surviver and i wont let this stop me. i just wish i knew what triggers the nightmares.
#ptsdisreal 
#sexualassaultisnojoke 
#metoo

text:
071018 part 2.
...after a very short waiting time, his mother knocked on my door saying the police is there looking for me. i told her to tell them to come upstairs. i wasnt going to open the door to her. god knows what they will do to me. so the police called my name and i opened the door. i told the female officer what happened before they came and she said we will wait for you no matter how long if you can call your friend to pick you up. dont worry she said. the male officer assured me with a nod. he went downstairs and my husband's mother was talking to the officer. i could hear her talk to him. she was completely unempathic like his son. that moment the female officer was guarding my room while i pack my stuff. it was funny that, that moment was a revelation to me: the reason why my husband is the way he is has always been because of his mother. exactly the same personality. no empathy and manipulative. i packed my stuff and told the officer it would be easier to take uber. so i packed only what sofia and i needed. i was shaking in anger for what suddenly has dawned on me. i saw what i needed to see. finally, i packed everything and the officer told me she will carry it for me. i told her they are too heavy and she told me to trust her because she lifts anything way bigger. i said okay. she took all my stuff downstairs and the male officer made sure that as i walk out of the house that nobody was there to stop me. i of course only took sofia with me while the driver and the officers helped me and the male officer secured sofia's seat because the carseat base wasnt available in the car. i left my baby's stroller and most of her stuff. my husband's mother was trying to desuade the officer to not let me take sofia and she was asking for an address where im taking my baby. i said i will text her son. the officer said "she can take her child with her whenever she wants because it's her baby". the officers escorted me out as my husband's mother was glaring at me like a psychopath. she was acting so calm with a smile on her face. btw, i have more to tell you about how they've been acting  at home... to be continued...

text:
07102018 part 3
when my ex husband's family came in august everything went downhill. everytime from 2015, 2016, to 2018 when they come together everything becomes really difficult for me. my ex becomes very abusive. he intimidates me & even tries to advance towards me as if he was going to hurt me. let me begin here. they came at almost midnight in august 17 need to check the date. i was so tired because i was with the baby the whole day without help. my ex wouldnt hire help. he said i should pay for it. i was on my 7th week of recovery postpartum. he also wouldnt buy a changing table because he loves to save money even if its to help me recover. i had to bend down everytime when changing the baby because the bed is lower than a changing table. my back was hurting so bad. when they finally came from the airport i was dead tired. sofia was in my arms because she wakes up when i put her down on the bed. i didnt know that time that i already violated his customs in serbia. later on in one of our repetitive email converstaions (we dont talk in person, its impossoble!), he actually expected me to be at the door welcoming his family to our home. seriously? after having no sleep since i pushed the baby out he expects this from me?! and he reiterates that i did not bring the baby down with me. i did! the guy is either having amnesia or just really mental. my ex put sofia on the corner in her cradle. his sister immediately asked me if i usually leave the baby there the whole night. my mind was in awe by such a question. who does that? a newborn left in a cradle/rocker the whole night? she asked if sofia has her own crib? i said yes she has. i really thought things got lost in translation because as my ex always says "english is not our first language" everytime he is confronted with the truth. somehow her question made me realize that between them there is also lack of communication. for how much they can talk they actually do not communicate!😅 how can they not know that they will be sleeping in my baby's room? if my ex told them his sister would know if sofia has a room then she must have a crib! babies dont sleep on the floor! to be continued...

a newborn left in a cradle/rocker the whole night? she asked if sofia has her own crib? i said yes she has. i really thought things got lost in translation because as my ex always says "english is not our first language" everytime he is confronted with the truth. somehow her question made me realize that between them there is also lack of communication. for how much they can talk they actually do not communicate!😅 how can they not know that they will be sleeping in my baby's room? if my ex told them his sister would know if sofia has a room then she must have a crib! babies do not sleep on the floor! to be continued...

i was told not post this but for all of us women who are experiencing domestic violence this is for you! #domesticviolence
...so his sister left my room finally & decided to go to chicago for many days. meanwhile my neighbors' mom just came for a visit for 6 months and since i met her she's been giving me soups almost everyday. my ex knows its part of our culture to give food to new moms. we dont let them work until they have recovered! the neighbors have been giving me food eversince but all of a sudden, my husband is pissed that i receive food from them?!!! he opened the door and told the neighbor to stop giving me food & instead to give me the recipe so i can make it at home. "we have food here at home" he said. i was so embarassed. instead of saying thank you he reprimanded the old woman. i apologized immediately. you see when your parents didnt teach you good moral values? or growing up in hatred and atheism? he has hit me more than 3 times in a span of four years. once with a towel, a shirt, then his big hand landed on my left ear with a big ringing sound. i wanted to call the police but i didnt want to hurt his immigration status. truth be told i'm his 3rd wife. for a 35 year old man who has been married 3 times and who constantly blames his partners for being bipolar? now i know why, because my ex tells me everytime that i'm crazy! now i dont believe him for having his own diagnoses of his ex wife. im sure she wasnt bipolar but that my ex was at fault in those marriages. he is not capable of empathy, sympathy, he is very impulsive, angry, he puts you down everytime, he calls you names, he lies to get out of trouble, doesnt admit his mistakes no matter what, he doesnt even see his faults. he cannot see parallelism in situations, and he needed help with his studies for 1 year and 6 months---i was helping him all the time bringing his projects at my work and then coming home running straight to the kitchen to make dinner. i used to carry 30 kilos of clothes to the basement to wash all his clothes. he wouldnt let me wash until the laundry is overflowing because he wants to save some quarters! he took $4500 from me 4 years ago...tbcont...

...to pay for my share that i didnt pay for 9 months of not working. afterall i was doing for him he wanted money! i couldnt enroll in school and couldnt pursue my phd due to having little to no money but he couldnt wait until i was settled. aside from that he started saying foul words "fu** you", calls me "b****", "w****", and many other unthinkable words and names. if this is normal in their family, it's not with mine! esp. given the fact that he was only my second boyfriend. i dont party, i dont smoke, i dont drink any type of alcoholic drinks either; the guy is mental! once i wanted to go out because he doesnt take me out at all especially in the first 3 years, i wanted to see the cherry blossoms festival two years ago but knowing how impatient and unforgiving he is he was angry  the whole time because of the traffic. he was angry with me too because i wanted something "difficult" even if it was a free event; my ex would never pay a penny if he could avoid it.
...going back to august and october event: he was expecting me to have breakfast, lunch & dinner with his family after all that has happened in the first 48 hours of their arrival. i wouldnt. 1.nobody apoligized 2.nobody was helping me 3.he comes angry into the room and when i talk back he advances toward me so i tell him i will call the police 4.he tells his family how inadequate i am 5.he became even more aggressive in action & in speech 6.there were days in august when he didnt even look at sofia 7.they take sofia out on a 90 degrees heat (so hot his dad fell on the ground!) 8.sofia came home with a scraped thigh which he said my nails caused 9.his mother takes sofia out on a rainy day 10.he defends his mother and sister instead of apologizing for their mistakes 11.sofia constantly misses her feedings at 7 weeks of age when they take her with them 12.they wont give her back to me until 10:30 pm 13. he was shaking sofia when she's crying!!! 14.he burps her by squeezing her until she is gasping for breath 15.he doesnt change her diaper for hours when they take her from me 16.he feeds her with the bottle upright and her head tilted upwards in a very dangerous choking hazard position...tbc...

text_retweet:
straight talk from our brand head and boss lady @atikaa_ahluwalia to show you that domestic violence happens to more people than you can imagine, and that taking back the power can transmutate the experience into one that brings growth, strength and an unshakeable sense of self 💫
repost @atikaa_ahluwalia
.
i was attacked by a man i was in a significant relationship with. pushed, thrown on the ground, kicked, held in a chokehold, different things on different days. in all my life before that, i never imagined myself as someone who could be physically abused. i mean, i'm educated, outspoken and independent. i travel the world and read vogue magazine. stuff like this just couldn’t happen to me. right? 
wrong. and how. it started with the shouting and the pushing. then came the things (including the breakfast i'd just made) that would be sent flying across the room. my cell phone would be taken away. messages from my family erased before i could see them. a couple of months into the relationship, i found myself on the floor one day, my tail bone hurting because i had just been kicked. in that one moment on the floor i remember thinking – i’ve read about this kind of thing in agony aunt columns. is this what they call physical abuse? no, no, no. that’s for those financially dependent, meek types that have had the misfortune of marrying big, mean looking men. this can’t be that. even though i had a ominous feeling that something was incredibly wrong, i told myself it's going to be okay tomorrow. 
it never really did. one day, i decided that i had had enough. i was leaving. that’s when i was held in a chokehold against the wall and told to ‘try and leave now’. the funny thing is. i still didn’t. i stayed another 90 days. after all, i ‘loved’ him. and believed that he ‘loved’ me in his own twisted way too. 
the picture you see above is me today. on my unique life journey and blissfully abuse-free. 
i left my abuser years ago and the day i did, i began a new, wonderful, painful, spiritual and magical journey that was possible because of the one thing that i’d like to share with all of you. hope.
do watch this space 🙏🏼
love,
atikaa
.

name: Eina Ahluwalia
tweet_full:
straight talk from our brand head and boss lady @atikaa_ahluwalia to show you that domestic violence happens to more people than you can imagine, and that taking back the power can transmutate the experience into one that brings growth, strength and an unshakeable sense of self 💫
repost @atikaa_ahluwalia
.
i was attacked by a man i was in a significan not relationship with. pushed, thrown on the ground, kicked, held in a chokehold, different things on different days. in all my life before that, i never imagined myself as someone who could be physically abused. i mean, i am educated, outspoken and independent. i travel the world and read vogue magazine. stuff like this just couldn’t happen to me. right? 
wrong. and how. it started with the shouting and the pushing. then came the things (including the breakfast i'd just made) that would be sent flying across the room. my cell phone would be taken away. messages from my family erased before i could see them. a couple of months into the relationship, i found myself on the floor one day, my tail bone hurting because i had just been kicked. in that one moment on the floor i remember thinking – i’ve read about this kind of thing in agony aunt columns. is this what they call physical abuse? no, no, no. that’s for those ficially dependent, meek types that have had the misfortune of marrying big, mean looking men. this can’t be that. even though i had a ominous feeling that something was incredibly wrong, i told myself it is going to be okay tomorrow. 
it never really did. one day, i decided that i had had enough. i was leaving. that’s when i was held in a chokehold against the wall and told to ‘try and leave now’. the funny thing is. i still didn’t. i stayed another 90 days. after all, i ‘loved’ him. and believed that he ‘loved’ me in his own twisted way too. 
the picture you see above is me today. on my unique life journey and blissfully abuse-free. 
i left my abuser years ago and the day i did, i began a new, wonderful, painful, spiritual and magical journey that was possible because of the one thing that i’d like to share with all of you. hope.
do watch this space 🙏🏼
love,
atikaa
.

#totemhope
#timesup #mytruth

text:
my ptsd has been in overdrive these past few weeks. 
the global conversation around sexual assault is so important, but it’s survivors who suffer most from that conversation. 
i keep thinking things are calming down (for me, anyhow) 
but then something will happen and i’m suddenly feeling not safe and angry and shaky and nauseous and all the things that come with the way my ptsd manifests. 
i’ve been down on myself about it lately, for not pulling through this patch better or sooner or whatever other self-blaming nonsense also accompanies ptsd. 
but then, this morning, a friend got really honest about how their post-kavanaugh flare up is still affecting them, and i instantly felt so much less alone. 
so, i decided to write this today, in case you too are feeling stuck and down on yourself, and needed a reminder that:
• you didn’t choose this
• you don’t get to choose how you’re triggered, how your body responds to those triggers, or how long their effects will last • now is a time to be kind to yourself, meet your physical needs, so your body feels safe, and surround yourself with situations and people who make you feel safe. 
you’re a warrior. 
you’ve made it this far. 
keep fighting. 
it won’t always be this hard. •
📷: @kerenhitterman_photography •
[kelly is dressed as eowyn from lord of the rings, sword in hand, staring off into the distance]
•
#ptsd #ptsdrecovery #ptsdsurvivor #metoo #believesurvivors #timesup #eowyn #iamnoman #warrior #warriorwoman #lotr

text:
my latest essay on #columnofstrength is out on @monument_lab! check out my thoughts on the recent international controversy over a monument in san francisco, its implications for the #metoo movement @metoomvmt , and why public speech and monuments are a matter of #genderequality. .
.
excerpt: the bronze sculptural group, column of strength, commemorates the young women and girls who were kidnapped and forced into sexual slavery by the japanese empire during world war ii. the monument was commissioned by the comfort women justice coalition and sculpted by artist steven whyte in 2017. the older woman off to the side is a portrait of korean activist kim hak soon, who was enslaved during the war. kim hak soon was one of the first women to come forward in august 1991 to speak publicly about japan’s war crimes and sexual violence, stating: “until now, i did not have the courage to speak, even though there are so many things i want to say.” #metoo #sanfrancisco #osaka #kimhaksoon #comfortwomen (socalled) #소녀상 #미투 #오사카 #김학순 📸: steven whyte 2017

text:
terça-feira 2 a canadense donna strickland foi a terceira mulher a ganhar o prêmio de física, depois de marie curie em 1903 e maria goeppert-mayer em 1963. ela dividiu uma metade do prêmio com gérard mourou (orientador de seu trabalho desenvolvido como tese de doutorado em 1985) por criar um método de gerar pulsos laser ultracurtos e de alta intensidade que abriram novas áreas de pesquisa e conduziram a muitas aplicações industriais e médicas e hoje são usadas rotineiramente em todas as cirurgias oculares a laser. a outra metade foi concedida ao estadunidense arthur ashkin – o mais idoso vencedor do nobel, com 94 anos – por outra pesquisa sobre lasers dos anos 1980 que resultou em pinças ópticas capazes de manipular objetos tão minúsculos quanto vírus, bactérias e organelas celulares.

no dia seguinte, a estadunidense frances h. arnold foi a quinta mulher a conseguir o galardão de química – a primeira foi igualmente marie curie, em 1911. recebeu metade do prêmio como pioneira da evolução dirigida de enzimas, trabalho de 1993 com o qual se reproduziu e acelerou em laboratório o processo de mutação e seleção natural para forçar bactérias a segregar enzimas previamente projetadas a partir das quais se pode obter a fabricação ambientalmente menos agressiva de substâncias químicas, produtos farmacêuticos e combustíveis renováveis. a outra metade foi dividida entre o estadunidense george smith e o britânico gregory p. winter pela criação em 1985 do método de seleção e isolamento de (vírus) bacteriófagos (phage display), usado para injetar informação genética em bactérias e forçá-las a produzir as proteínas desejadas.

a dupla conquista, obtida com pesquisas de enorme importância teórica e prática, importa mais por chegar quando os avanços recentes do feminismo na ampliação do espaço para as mulheres em posições de prestígio – e também campanhas por igualdade e respeito, como a #metoo iniciada em 2017 – despertam em conservadores com privilégios ameaçados uma reação amarga cujo papel no crescimento de movimentos neofascistas por todo o mundo, inclusive no brasil, eua e euro, onde partidos de extrema-direita são hoje parte de coalizões de governo em países como a aust.

text:
för ett år sen sa jag och många med mig att "det är dags att gå från feministiskt självförsvar till maskulint självansvar". samtidigt svarade endast 14 procent av männen (och 23 procent av kvinnorna) ja på frågan: "har #metoo-uppropet påverkat dig och ditt beteende?” i ipsos senaste mätning.

det är alltså fler kvinnor än män som anser att de förändrat sitt beteende.... det här är inte okej.

hur tar en maskulint ansvar då?

vi på @makeequal ställde därför frågan "hur kan du som man bidra till en samtyckeskultur?" där vi fick in över 1000 svar. 
dessa svar publicerade vi i vår bok #alltviintepratarom, tillsammans med utmaningar, samtalsguider och intervjuer med män som vågar ta i de jobbiga och känsliga frågorna på riktigt. för att börja med sig själv - tillsammans med andra män.

har ni inte läst boken, lyssnat på podden eller spelat spelet än? har du inte haft en #killmiddag än? finns nu för yngre, pappor, arbetsplatser, på engelska, offentliga, med vänner etc.

här kommer info varje grej. sprid gärna så att inga män kommer undan med uttalanden som "ja men vad ska jag göra åt det?". #metoo #makeequal #alltviintepratarom #killmiddag #detbörjarmedmig

text:
män släpper sifo-undersökning och studie om #metoo
imorgon (läs: tisdag, 16 oktober) håller män ett frukostseminarium som vi kallar “#metoo – ett år senare”. där presenterar vi resultaten från en nygjord undersökning av mäns attityder efter #metoo, utförd av sifo, på uppdrag av män, samt premiärsläpper studien ”men, masculinity and #metoo”, som redogör för hur de nordiska länderna hanterade #metoo.
nu har det gått ett år sedan #metoo startade och blev till en kraftfull rörelse. så var står vi nu, ett år senare? har #metoo-uppropens berättelser lett till att män förändrat sitt beteende? har män ökat sitt engagemang för jämställdhet och mot våld? och anser män i sverige att de som grupp har något särskilt ansvar för det sexualiserade våld och trakasserier som män utsätter andra för?
frukostseminariet äger rum på saturnus konferens i stockholm och är dessvärre fullsatt – däremot kommer vi att livesända! håll utkik på män.se samt vår facebook.
alla på plats får en tryckt version av studien “men, masculinity and #metoo” med sig hem. den finns även att hämta kostnadsfritt på mäns kontor i hammarby sjöstad, stockholm.
vi ses imorgon på plats, eller i cyberrymden! ✨

text:
those against #metoo often point out 2 ‘flaws’ in the movement.

the claims shared are treated without question. no one asks, “hey, is this really true?” or questions the reliability of the story. those who then never truly committed the crime, but were claimed as having done otherwise, would become victims of both circumstance and witch hunts because no one bothered to fact check or hear the other side of the story. 
the movement fusses over actions that are, at most, annoying flirting. due to the possible consequences that can be faced for sexual misconduct, some argue that several of the stories are blown out of proportion and the actions of the individual involved were simply flirting that was, at the worst, persistent. however, never harmful. mainly, flirting should never land someone 4 years in jail (at the least). (2)

text:
давно не было поста знакомства)
я оля, мне 34 года. живу в городе миассе, челябинской области.
почти 3 года я занимаюсь детским текстилем🤗 моя цель - украсить и сделать кроватки ваших малышей уютными, красивыми, а главное безопасными💕 за это время мои изделия разлетелись по многочисленным городам россии и нескольким стран мира✈️🌎 большое количество отзывов и фотоотчетов от вас, мои дорогие заказчицы, вдохновляют меня и помогают мне развиваться и двигаться дальше! 
у меня 2 сына: 1,9 и 6 лет. они иногда появляются в моей ленте😉 
закончила факультет управления. хотела работать в администрации, но судьба сложилась иначе, чему я безумно рада 😀
я трудоголик 💪🏼любое свободное время стараюсь проводить с умом. вообще жизнь очень коротка, чтобы тратить время попусту. я все время стараюсь чему-то учится, развиваться. видеоролики и книги по саморазвитию мои самые любимые❤️
а теперь вы расскажите немного о себе👇🏼 из какого вы города, чем занимаетесь? 
#cottonmiracle_история

text:
after spending a crisp fall yesterday out on the campaign trail, i took an hour to grocery shop (seriously love this task) and then go home for dinner with (some of) the family. i roasted a chicken & baked a cake to show my family,who have been supporting me through this hectic campaign season, that i love them deeply. 
last night was also the nh state democratic party’s “eleanor roosevelt dinner” which i had been so very excited to attend, until the planning committee choose alec baldwin as the keynote speaker. immediately i knew i was out. while he does an amusing comedic interpretation of our president, his long sordid history of abuse of his daughter, dismissal of the seriousness of the #metoo survivors, mocking sexual harassment and reflexive racism & homophobia in times of stress are disqualifiers for me to buy a ticket to this event. this was a great disappointment to me, not having the opportunity to spend time with some people i truly admire & respect but alec baldwin was more than a guest i could steer clear of at a party, he was the headliner on the program. i am disappointed in the planners who choose this divisive man to sell tickets in the first year this annual event is finally named for a woman. i sincerely hope better choices are made next year. #nhpolitics
name: Debra Altschiller

text:
#스쿨미투 #metoo #withyou
우리는 서로의 용기다. [참여방법]
1.#스쿨미투 #metoo #withyou 해시태그와 함께 자신의 연대문을 작성한다.
2. 인증사진을 찍고 게시한다.
3. 최소 3명이상 태그한다.
4. 태그 받은 사람은 참여한다.

또 다른 용기에 @ji5nizzi @im_whddms @real__sojeong @seung_mini811 @k_sumini @arim427 을 지목합니다.

ㅡ
고등학교 때, 내 팔 안 쪽을 꼬집던 선생님이 있었다. 뭔가 불쾌했지만 그렇다고 말하기는 애매하고 왠지 부끄럽기도 하고, 뭐가 불쾌한지 설명할 수 없어 그냥 찝찝한 채로 넘어간 적이 있다. 사실 나는 선생님이 내가 착한 학생이라 칭찬하는 줄 알았다. 왜 아무도 그건 불쾌한거라고, 그 불쾌함을 말해도 된다고 해주지 않았는가? 나는 아직도 그 때의 장면을 잊지 못한다. 학교 현장에서 가장 존중받고 보호받아야 마땅한 학생들을 괴롭히지 마라. 그들은, 우리들은 당신들의 세계를 부수어 낼 것이다.

👩🏼‍🍳in pratica👨‍🍳
quanti libri sono stati scritti sull’alimentazione sana, quanti medici predicano di mangiare bene, quante ricette light ci sono in internet, quanti consigli vi danno vostra madre, le colleghe, il tg e il personal trainer! che confusione! la teoria sembra la conoscano tutti ma poi quando mancano 10 minuti all’ora di cena, quando siamo al supermercato in preda alla fame, quando vogliamo cucinare qualcosa di sano senza che ce lo tirino dietro cosa facciamo⁉️ la teoria è nulla senza la pratica... per questo motivo con passione e umiltà ho creato @youmum_official, 10 anni di esperienza al vostro servizio 😛
in sede o a domicilio 🍒lezioni di cucina naturale(panificazione, colazioni, dolci, cereali, verdure, legumi e tanto altro). 👨‍🍳incontri singoli o di gruppo 🥣svezzamento naturale
visita il sito (link in bio), i miei corsi sono preziosi, (per i contenuti e non per il costo)😝 questo stile alimentare arricchirà solo voi stessi 🤩. io ci sarei venuta a fare un corso da me quando volevo imparare a cucinare 😉

text:
former miss universe sushmita sen is proud of the women who have spoken up about their unsavoury experiences, as a result of the metoo movement. she says now is the time to listen, believe and let justice prevail.

sushmita interacted with the media at the bombay times fashion week here on sunday.

she said she doesn't find the revelations coming up in context of the metoo movement shocking at all as people were aware of these things for long. "it is going to be shocking every single time, but we are also not ignorant people. it's not like we didn't know these things were happening in india and in the world. i think what is more shocking that we did not listen to it for so long and that we didn't do anything about it. this is the start, and you have to listen, believe and let justice prevail," sushmita said.
#sushmitasen #sush #missuniverse #metoo #instagram #instagrammer #instagrammers #instagrammersgallery #instagallery #shocking

text:
la dissociation 
c’est une « séparation fonctionnelle entre des éléments psychique ou mentaux qui sont habituellement réunis. 
ainsi, la prise en compte de la réalité et du vécu ce déconnecte (pensée, jugement, sentiment), de façon temporaire ou durable, pour supporter un traumatisme psychique.
au moment de l'agression, le stress est tellement extrême qu'il représente un danger vital. 
pour le stopper, le cerveau fait «disjoncter» le circuit émotionnel, et la mémoire avec. la victime est comme paralysée. »

quand j’étais dans ce lit, c’étais bien moi. c’étais mon corps. mais je regardais la scène sur le cotée, d’en haut.. comme si j’étais dans un film, comme si j’étais une troisième personne qui assisté à la violence de l’acte. je ne voulais pas y croire. ça ne pouvait pas m’arriver, pas à moi. pas pour ma première fois... on appelle ça la dissociation.
j’ai appris ce mot, il y’a quelques semaines. 
j’ai toujours ressentis un vide, un mal-être comme si je n’existais pas. j’étais là sans être là. j’allais mal, je me suis dit que c’était pas normal. je culpabiliser en me disant que j’avais tout pour être heureuse. mais que j’avais une douleur persistante au fond de moi. 
je savais que cet événement avait existé mais il est été comme noyé. 
j’étais dans l’incapacité de parler. 
comme si c’était irréel, comme si ça ne c’était pas vraiment passé.

j’ai vécue des bons moments, parfois des moments heureux. mais dans l’ensemble, il y’a toujours eu quelque chose qui m’empêche de vivre pleinement. j’ai l’impression d’être condamnées à jouer un personnage qui n’est pas moi. mais que j’aimerai être. 
l’image que je renvoie aux autres personnes n’est pas moi. 
je fais énormément d’efforts pour tenir debout. je suis comme coupées de moi-même. 
je suis la, présente. mais je n’existe plus. .
.
.
.

text:
i am all for people standing up against their abusers but this whole #metoo movement has become the biggest and most ridiculous thing i've ever witnessed in my 30 years.

if we as a nation keep going like this, our 6 year old daughter or son could be the next "victim" just because one child tried to squeeze past the other child in the lunch line and something accidentally touched.

and it's not just this movement, have u watched the news lately? smdh. it breaks my heart that my 3 girls are going to have to grow up in this world and in 12 years when my oldest turns 18 i dont even want to imagine the nonsense that's going to be going on then. 
seriously let's rewind the clocks and go back to the 60s. 
i have a ton more i could say but i dont wanna start drama, just wanted to throw my feelings out there 🤷‍♀️🤷‍♀️🤷‍♀️

text:
union minister m.j. akbar, a former editor, is the first politician to be named in the flood of sexual allegations propping from the #metoo movement wave.
.
from forcibly trying to kiss young interns to conducting interviews in hotel rooms, a dozen women journalists have accused him of inappropriate behaviour during his stint as an editor.
.
however, after returning from his african tour, he clearly denied all these allegations stating them to be baseless, false and fabricated. he further claimed a political conspiracy behind these allegations. “why has this storm risen a few months before a general election? is there an agenda? you be the judge. these false, baseless and wild allegations have caused irreparable damage to my reputation and goodwill”
.
.
.
.
.

text:
the forest had a maw so gaping
sabertoothed branches ravenous
never to enter mothers would beg
it is forbidden fathers would warn.
was she foolish, was she willful
to be so deep in under dark boughs?
rebel or careless, so much to blame?
living in that wolf shadow a ghostling
scorned and cursed in hushed breaths
accusers beholding her moving bones
cannot grasp what happened there
they cannot accept the evidence 
that proves the forest came to her.
.
.
poem "the forest" by t.stark 
artwork by @rivuletpaper .
.

text:
#الأمم_المتحدة تطرح آليات المساءلة عن العنف الجنسي أثناء النزاع: تحديد الفجوات النظرية والعملية في الولاية القانونية الوطنية في المنطقة العربية

يشكل الاغتصاب ، والاستعباد الجنسي ، والاتجار ، والزواج القسري والمبكر أمثلة من الجرائم الجنسية المرتكبة ضد النساء والفتيات ، والتي تزداد خلال حالات النزاع. إن أضرار هذه الأعمال على حياتهم تكون طويلة المدى . فالوصمة الاجتماعية والافتقار إلى القنوات القانونية الملائمة غالباً ما تترك الضحايا دون دعم حيوي ، مع عواقب وخيمة على أنفسهم وعائلاتهم ومجتمعاتهم المحلية. كيفية معالجة احتياجات الضحايا والناجين من مثل هذه الجرائم من خلال الوصول الشامل إلى العدالة والدعم ، وكيفية تشجيع الناجين على التقدم هي بعض الأسئلة التي نوقشت في ملخص اجتماع الخبراء هذا.

نظمت منظمة الأمم المتحدة للمرأة وبرنامج الأمم المتحدة الإنمائي وفريق خبراء الأمم المتحدة المعني بسيادة القانون والعنف الجنسي في حالات النزاع اجتماعًا لمدة يومين لمناقشة المساءلة عن العنف الجنسي أثناء النزاع في سياق الشرق الأوسط في أبريل 2018. من بين أشياء أخرى ، أكد الخبراء الحاجة لفصل قضية "الجنس" عن "العنف الجنسي" من أجل ضمان استجابة قضائية ملائمة ، ولتقسيم الجريمة وتحويل العار من الضحية إلى الجاني. كما اتفق الخبراء على أهمية العدالة الشاملة والشاملة للناجين من العنف الجنسي ومجتمعاتهم.

tw: sexualisierte gewalt
.
#metoo ist ein hashtag, das ab dem 15. oktober 2017 millionenfach verwendet wurde. kurz vorher war bekannt geworden, dass mehrere frauen den filmproduzenten harvey weinstein der sexuellen belästigung, nötigung oder der vergewaltigung beschuldigten.
die schauspielerin @milano_alyssa ermutigte daraufhin auf twitter frauen, diesen hashtag zu nutzen, um auf das ausmaß sexueller belästigung und sexueller übergriffe aufmerksam zu machen. .
#metoo trendete in mindestens 85 nationen. laut twitter haben in den usa 45 prozent der nutzer*innen freund*innen, die dieses hashtag verwendet hätten. in einigen nicht-englischsprachigen ländern haben sich statt #metoo landessprachliche alternativen durchgesetzt, zum beispiel #balancetonporc in frankreich. auf deutsch übersetzt heißt das "verpfeif’ dein schwein".
.
erstmals war das hashtag 2006 auf myspace von der aktivistin @taranajaneen verwendet worden. sie wollte damals mit ihrer kampagne empathie unter schwarzen frauen fördern, die sexuellen missbrauch erfahren hatten. ~ sabrina
.
[bildbeschreibung: die zeichnung zeigt neun personen (augenscheinlich frauen) unterschiedlichen alters, die gemeinsam die buchstaben "me too" tragen.]
.
#metoo #sexuelleselbstbestimmung #feminismus #innenansicht #innenansichtmagazin

hur startades #metoo?

det var en kvinna vid namn tarana burke som startade #metoo 2006 på hemsidan just be inc. metoo var menad att rikta sig till unga kvinnor och främst rasifierade som blivit utsatta för sexuella övergrepp. hon ville att dessa kvinnor skulle förstå att dem inte var ensamma i sin utsatthet, snarare tvärtom upplysa om hur vanliga dessa övergrepp är. ——————————————————————-
så skaparen av #metoo är tarana burke och kort sagt går det att säga att kampanjen har några år på nacken. men trots detta så var det inte förrän förra året som den verkligen bubblade upp, kanske för att tiden var mer mogen att ta emot ett budskap som detta, vem vet?
——————————————————————-
den tionde oktober 2017 uppmanade alyssa milano alla som ofredats sexuellt att hashtaga metoo på sociala medier, en katalysator som gjorde att kampanjen exploderade. denna uppmaning kom även i samband med de första anklagelserna mot harvey weinsten.
name: KGs feministiska förening!

text:
lewinsky affair not an abuse of power, says hillary clinton
#african
lewinsky affair not an abuse of power, says hillary clinton file photo of monica lewinsky hillary clinton has said her husband bill’s affair with former white house intern monica lewinsky was not an abuse of power and he was right to not resign from the us presidency in the wake of the scandal. the two-decades-old episode has come under renewed scrutiny in the #metoo era, with critics questioning whether the power imbalance between a sitting president and an intern made it impossible for the relationship to be considered consensual. some, like new york senator kirsten gillibrand, have said that clinton should have stepped down after he was impeached by a republican-controlled house in late 1998 for lying about the affair. but speaking on cbs news on sunday, former presidential candidate and secretary of state hillary clinton said she disagreed. “absolutely not,” she replied when asked whether her husband should have resigned. pressed on whether the relationship was an abuse of power, clinton said: “no, no” and noted that lewinsky, who was 22-years-old at the time, “was an adult.” “there was an investigation and it, as i believe, came out in the right place,” she added. in 1999, the senate held a month-long trial of president clinton that ultimately fell well short of the two-thirds majority required to convict and remove him from office. lewinsky, for her part, long maintained the affair was consensual, but in an essay published in vanity fair earlier this year wrote she had begun to re-evaluate that view. bill clinton has also been accused by several other women of sexual misconduct in cases going back to the 1970s, prompting a reckoning of his place in history by democrats in light of the #metoo and time’s up movements. afp  the post lewinsky affair not an abuse of power, says hillary clinton appeared first on channels television. source: channelstv

ذهن مریض فمینیستی! مادر شدن یک انگ و جرم نیست! اتهامات بدون مدرک آزار جنسی مرد رو تا ابد تحت نام آزارگر جنسی قرار میده و امکان تحصیل و کار رو ازش می گیره و جایگاه اجتماعیش رو نابود می کنه. ولی چون تفکر فمینیستی بر انتقام گرفتن از مردها بنا شده، این دوتا رو کنار هم میذاره و میگه حالا که زنها به خاطر بچه دار شدن مجبورن کمتر کار کنن، پس این به اون در! یه لحظه یادشون نمی افته که به ازای هر مادر و فرزند، یک پدر هست که داره عمده ی درآمدش رو به زن و فرزند اختصاص میده تا از هر لحاظ دچار مشکل نشن!
.
.
.
.
یه نکته دیگه رو هم اضافه کنم: جمله ی "مردانی ‌که کارشان را به خاطر آزار جنسی همکارشان از دست می دهند" یک مغلطه ی موذیانست! درستش اینه"مردهایی که کارشان را بابت "اتهام" آزار جنسی از دست می دهند..."! .
.
.
‌. #فمینیسم #فمینیست #می_تو #metoo #برابری_جنسیتی #مرد_ستیزی #حقوق_مردان #سکسیزم #سکسیسم #آزار_جنسی

text:
#metoo: nifty companies reported 588 cases of sexual harassment in fy18

a majority of complaints came in from it sector employees

among companies, the information technology (it) sector accounted for 244 of the total complaints filed. wipro, for instance, reported 101 cases. the high number is reflective of the gender ratios as well, since it companies have a higher percentage of women employees than the others.

similarly, traditional engineering and oil & gas companies had a low incidence of sexual harassment complaints being filed. these sectors employ 30 percent or less women as a portion of their total workforce

#sensex
#niftyfifty #stocks #brand #sexualharasement

among companies, the information technology (it) sector accounted for 244 of the total complaints filed. wipro, for instance, repoed 101 cases. the high number is reflective of the gender ratios as well, since it companies have a higher percentage of women employees than the others.

similarly, traditional engineering and oil & gas companies had a low incidence of sexual harassment complaints being filed. these sectors employ 30 percent or less women as a poion of their total workforce

text: #metoo: प्रिया रमानी के खिलाफ कोर्ट पहुंचे एमजे अकबर, मानहानि का केस किया हालांकि एमजे अकबर इस बात का भी स्पष्टीकरण देना होगा कि उन्होंने सिर्फ प्रिया रमानी के खिलाफ ही क्यों आपराधिक मानहानि का मुकदमा दायर किया है, जबकि उन पर आरोप लगाने वाली महिला है तकरीबन एक दर्जन के आसपास है.#metoo खुलासे के तहत कई महिला पत्रकारों द्वारा यौन शोषण का आरोप झेल रहे केन्द्रीय मंत्री एमजे अकबर ने पत्रकार प्रिया रमानी के खिलाफ आपराधिक मानहानि का मुकदमा दर्ज कराया है. एमजे अकबर ने दिल्ली की पटियाला हाउस कोर्ट में भारतीय दंड संहिता की धारा 499 और 500 के तहत आपराधिक मानहानि का केस दर्ज कराया है. आईपीसी की इन धाराओं के तहत दोषी पाये जाने पर दो साल की सजा का प्रावधान है. केंद्रीय मंत्री ने लॉ फर्म करंजावाला एंड कंपनी के जरिये पत्रकार प्रिया रमानी पर केस दर्ज कराया है.दिलचस्प यह भी है कि ख़ुद वकील करंजावाला के खिलाफ एक महिला वकील ने भी सेक्सुअल हरासमेंट के आरोप लगा रखे हैं. बता दें कि रविवार को केन्द्रीय मंत्री ने विदेश दौरे से लौटने के बाद अपने खिलाफ लगे यौन शोषण के आरोपों को निराधार और गलत बताया था. एमजे अकबर ने रविवार को ही कहा था कि वे ऐसा आरोप लगाने वाली पत्रकारों के खिलाफ कोर्ट जाएंगे.अकबर ने प्रिया रमानी के खिलाफ झूठे आरोप लगा कर बदनाम करने की साजिश रचने का मुकदमा दर्ज किया है. अपनी याचिका में एम जे अकबर ने कहा है कि 2016 में प्रधानमंत्री ने उन्हें मंत्री बनाया था. वो मध्यप्रदेश से राज्यसभा सांसद है. अकबर ने ये भी कहा कि उन्होंने अपने करियर में the making of india, kashmir behind the valley जैसी कई महत्वपूर्ण किताबे लिखीं है. उन्होंने याचिका में कहा, उन्होंने कहा कि इस महिला पत्रकार ने इस तरह के आरोप लगाकर, ट्वीट करके और आर्टिकल पब्लिश कराकर उनकी प्रतिष्ठा को नुकसान पहुचाया है. ये आरोप झूठे मानहानि करने वाले और बदनीयती से लगाये गए हैं. अकबर ने याचिका में यह भी कहा है कि ये सब एजेंडा से प्रेरित है. याचिका में कहा गया है कि उन पर लगाए गए आरोपों से ना केवल उनकी बदनामी हुई है बल्कि सालों की कडी मेहनत के बाद स्थापित सामाजिक और राजनीतिक प्रतिष्ठा को भी ठेस पहुंची है. याचिका में एमजे अकबर ने 6 गवाहों का भी जिक्र किया है. #news #politicalaffairsmedia #newdelhi
name: Political Affairs

text:
🤷🏾‍♀️ “why do you travel so much?”, someone asked. 💁🏾‍♀️ travel is my lifestyle priority because:
1. i am single (legally) not yet married with no kids.....why wait to live your best life once you’re anchored down by obligations to other human beings?
2. “you may delay, but time will not” ben franklin
3. traveling heals the soul and invigorates the spirit and after my #metoo saga i’m only focused on activities and people bringing me joy 
4. society has not been kind to me—this world belongs to me just as much as everyone else—this is my way of getting everything i want from the world while also making all of my (horribly failed) ex flings and past associates/haters think twice...
5. majority of my past life was spent “people pleasing” and trying to measure up to impossible double standards around being a black american woman—-this is my version of being happy, carefree, and living for self pleasure and discovery
🙋🏾‍♀️ 👙💫🏊🏾‍♂️⚓️⛵️🛩🌊🏖
#travelista #grandcayman #adventure #whyitravel #worldtraveler #bestlife #blessed #grateful #selfcare #selflove #selfexploration #explore #dream #travelnoir #secretphotographer #snorkeling #traveldiaries #baecation
name: Jordan Taylor

text:
(tw!) ✩★✩★
i år firar vi den första upplagan av metoo-dagen! dagen är ett intiativ av malin nordström som vill uppmärksamma metoo-rörelsen.
✩★✩★
rörelsen har genomgående syftat till att lyfta fram sexuella trakasserier och övergrepp mot kvinnor. dessa har i hög utsträckning tidigare tystats ned och större skuld har lagts på den person som utsatts än på den som begått övergreppet.
✩★✩★
en likande rörelse skapades år 2006 på myspace av kvinnorättsaktivisten tarana burke, som ville uppmärksamma sexuella trakasserier mot kvinnor som är poc (people of colour).
✩★✩★
rörelsen bredde ut sig 2017 efter avslöjanden om sexuella trakasserier och våldtäkter inom amerikansk filmindustri. genom hashtaggen #metoo uppmanade skådespelaren alyssa milano kollegor att på sociala medier delge sina erfarenheter av dittills nedtystade övergrepp, trakasserier och våldtäkter.
✩★✩★
har du blivit utsatt eller känner någon som blivit det? vi uppmanar er då att gå in på www.minupprättelse.se för att läsa mer om hjälp och stöd. 
#elevkar #kramfrånstyrelsen
•
•
•
(syntolkning: en mängd händer med orden ”me too” skrivna på handflatorna.)

text:
idag har det gått ett år sedan #metoo. under året som varit har vi i women for leaders varit ute och träffat många olika företag och vi vill uppmärksamma några positiva förändringar till följd av #metoo: - det har blivit mer legitimt att säga ifrån. - fler företag tar sitt ansvar och börjar utarbeta policys samt konkreta handlingsplaner.
- mediabevakningen på området har ökat och förhoppningsvis balanserats, som nu senast i finansbranchen. 
efter #metoo såg vi en tydlig uppgång på aktiviteter i de flesta företagsledningar, nu gäller det att fortsätta arbeta kontinuerligt. upp till bevis alla företag! 💫
.
.
.
#leadthechange #changethelead #payitforward #metoo 📸 @kyllerphoto

text:
heute vor 3jahren kamen bei 37+6 unsere zwillinge per kaiserschnitt zur welt.

das foto hat mein mann bereits ende der 35.ssw gemacht,es zeigt wieviel mein bauch leisten musste und leider habe ich kein finales bild,allerdings ist der bauch zum schluss noch etwas gewachsen. lange habe ich dieses bild niemanden gezeigt.

heute feiern wir den 3.geburtstag unserer zwillinge,bis hier hin war es ein langer weg. 
denn, die schwangerschaft war keine einfache,auch die geburt nicht.
erst vor ein paar monaten,konnt ich mein geburtsbericht einfordern und ihn ohne tränen lesen...ich bat eine hebamme mit uns den durch zu gehen und dabei kam das heraus was ich befürchtet hatte, ich bin leider in die interventions falle getappt. schlechte kommunikation und angstmacherei haben wohl dazu geführt,das obwohl ich 17monate zuvor spontan unseren ältesten sohn geboren habe und die kinder in schädellage lagen, der kaiserschnitt aus bequemlichkeit gemacht wurde.

ich habe lange damit gekämpft und war auch lange sauer auf mich selbst,das ich nicht die notbremse zog und das krankenhaus verlassen habe. 
zu keiner zeit ging es den kindern schlecht,sie waren einfach noch nicht soweit.

mir ist nun bewusst, jede mutter sollte auf sich hören, wenn man ein schlechtes gefühl hat und sich nicht wohl fühlt...
angst hat,weil die ärtze auf einen einreden, dann sollte man inne halten und überlegen,ob es der richtige ort ist,sein kind zugebären. denn man muss sich wohl fühlen ,um eine schöne geburt erleben zu können. manchmal sind es die umstände die es nicht zulassen spontan zu gebären,dennoch kann es und sollte all das aber selbstbestimmt und nicht fremdbestimmt passieren. 
denn es ist mein körper und ich bestimme wie ich unser kind zur welt bringen möchte. niemand sonst!

jetzt feiern wir nachher erstmal noch bei kaffee und kuchen und ich schaue mir unsere glücklichen kinder an und bin stolz darauf ihre mutter sein zu dürfen. ❤️ #metoo
#zwillingsmom
#happybirthday
#dafürhabeichdreijahregebraucht
#familylife
#zwillinge

fortsätter vårt arbete sida vid sida med alla dessa. frågan är fortfarande på dagordningen och stora samhällsinsatser behövs för att adressera grundproblemet med sexism, sexuella trakasserier och övergrepp samt konsekvenserna av detta i form av psykisk ohälsa.

text:
comment draguer une femme, un an après #metoo ? c'est la question à laquelle répond la journaliste et auteure fiona schmidt, dans son livre "l'amour après #metoo, traité de séduction à l'usage des hommes qui ne savent plus comment parler aux femmes"
.
plus qu'un simple guide de drague, fiona schmidt décortique dans cet ouvrage les rouages des relations hommes-femmes et comment on en est arrivé à un déséquilibre, subi de toutes parts : la séduction reste l'affaire des hommes et les femmes se positionnent comme des trophées, qui attendent seulement d'être décrochés
.
pour découvrir l'interview de @thefionaschmidt rdv sur notre site (lien dans la bio) !

text:
pride of place in the @vamuseum  medieval and renaissance galleries is vincenzo de rossi's sculpture of the rape of proserpina. visitors coo over the dynamism of bronze rendered into flesh, the ripple of perfectly formed renaissance anatomy in the god pluto and his victim proserpina - who was abducted to be his sex slave in the underworld while her mother wept. her gaze calls out for mercy and her outstretched arm says no as well as effectively displaying her graceful body. the dark god's face is focused on his depraved intentions and her toes curl in fear. where once i would have talked about this work as an example of skill in material exploitation or of an italian renaissance interest in the stories of the classical world, i now feel uncomfortable about how we collectively overlook the dark sexual violence it narrates and i'm not quite sure what we should do about it.
#rapeculture #rapeinarthistory #metoo #renaissance #sculpture #plutoandproserpina #isbeautyanexcuse?

text:
so yesterday i was traveling to boisar. a place near virar, mumbai. i was going to my grandmother's place.
i witnessed a thing which i would like to share.

i was travelling in a rickshaw from railway station to the destination where i wanted to reach,
i was sitting in the front with 3 other guys including the driver,

back part of the rickshaw was forcefully filled with 4 people, while the actual maximum capacity was of 3 people.

there were 2 teen girls on the left side, followed by one lady of almost 30-35 years of age, and then there was an old man aged between 55-60.

i am making myself clear here itself that i am not supporting or opposing any person or gender here, just read it till the end.

eventually like every other place in our country the roads were not in a good condition obviously,

because of which we were getting many jerks on the roads, eventually during one such big pot hole, the old man may have accidentally touched the lady which happened involuntarily ( i guessed so, i maybe wrong too) and if i guessed it wrong then he got what he deserved but also look at the other point of view.

so the lady immediately started shouting "how dare you touch me, you bloody cheap pervert" 
to which the man immediately apologized and said it was because of the pothole and not intentional.

she told the driver to stop and started yelling at the man that she knows what he was upto, every men is the same.

she told the man to come out to which the man refused and was also apologizing continuously that it wasn't intentional it was by mistake.

and suddenly 3-4 men appeared all of a sudden, they didn't arrive they just appeared all of a sudden which happens every time when there is a fight in our country because there are large number of unemployed people in our country and this is the only entertainment source they have.

the lady got inside and slapped the man and then the other 3-4 men took the matter in their hands "without even knowing what happened" they just took him out and started beating the hell out of him, he was already bald and a bit weak as his age was almost 55-60 and they were just beating him vigorously just because the lady slapped him. ⬇️⬇️⬇️

text:
tim sw senang sekali bisa dipertemukan dan berdiskusi tentang pacaran sehat dan citra tubuh positif dengan remaja-remaja keren dampingan gereja sidang jemaat allah parakletos di biak kota. .
.
meski di awalnya malu-malu, tapi lama-kelamaan jadi mulai bisa akrab. nah, salah satu hal yang jadi bahan diskusi kita adalah konsep kecantikan nih, guys. selama ini kan, kita banyak disajikan oleh media bahwa cantik itu katanya harus berkulit putih, rambut lurus, langsing, dll. nah, kami belajar bersama dan mendefinisikan ulang tentang konsep kecantikan dan saling memotivasi bahwa mencintai tubuh kita adalah yang terpenting. .
.
di akhir sesi ini, kami semua membuat 3 pujian untuk diri kita dan salah satu peserta memuji dirinya dengan berkata bahwa ia perempuan yang baik, berani, berkulit hitam dan berambut keriting dan itu adalah identitasnya sebagai orang papua.  keren, yah?
.
.
.

text:
recently, tanushree dutta's allegations against veteran actor nana patekar took the bollywood industry by storm and a lot of people have started calling out their abusers on social media. 
in the wake of this, dangal actor aamir khan had found out that a person he was supposed to work with in future, was called out in the #metoo movement. so, the actor has cut off all ties with the above mentioned person, and also cancelled the project. 
following this, he gave a statement regarding the me too issue, and clarified his stance. he said: "as creative people we have been committed to foregrounding and finding solutions to social issues, and at aamir khan productions we have always had a zero-tolerance policy towards sexual misconduct and predatory behaviour of any kind. we strongly condemn any act of sexual harassment, and equally we condemn any and all false accusations in such cases.

two weeks ago, when traumatic #metoo stories began emerging, it was brought to our attention that someone we were about to begin work with has been accused of sexual misconduct. upon enquiry we found that this particular case is subjudice, and that the legal process is in motion.

we are not an investigative agency, nor are we in any position to pass judgement on anyone - that is for the police and judiciary to do. so, without casting any aspersions on anyone involved in this case, and without coming to any conclusions about these specific allegations, we have decided to step away from this film.

we do not want our action to reflect in any manner on the people involved in this case.

we believe that this is an opportunity for the film industry to introspect and take concrete steps towards change. for far too long women have faced the brunt of sexual exploitation. it has to stop. in this regard we are committed to doing any and everything to make our film industry a safe and happy one to work in." - kiran rao and aamir khan

text:
तो क्या यह भी #metoo था ?

तारकेश्वरी सिन्हा की याद है आप को ? वही बिहार वाली ........... गज़ब की पर्लियामेंटेरियन थीं । उन की शेरो-शायरी से उन के भाषण ही नहीं , संसद भी गुंजायमान रहती थी । उन की शेरो शायरी , उन की सुंदरता , उन की दिलफरेब अदाएं , तिस पर उन का युवा होना चहुँ ओर चर्चा में रहता था । 
पंडित नेहरु के समय जब वह पहली बार सांसद चुन कर आईं तो एक दिन नेहरु के पी ए मथाई ने उन को फोन कर बताया कि पंडित जी आप से मिलना चाहते हैं । तारकेश्वरी बहुत खुश हुईं । तय समय पर वह पहुंचीं भी पंडित नेहरु से मिलने । लेकिन मथाई ने बहुत देर तक अपने पास ही बिठाए रखा और इधर-उधर की बातें करते रहे । मथाई की बातों से ऊब कर तारकेश्वरी ने पूछा कि आखिर कब मिलेंगे पंडित जी । मथाई ने बताया जल्दी ही । फिर कहा कि आइए तब तक आप को कुछ पेंटिंग दिखाते हैं। पेंटिंग रुम में जब मथाई के साथ वह पहुंचीं तो वहां बहुत सारी न्यूड पेंटिंग भी दीवार पर उपस्थित थीं , जिन्हें मथाई उन्हें दिखाने लगे । तारकेश्वरी सिनहा सहसा न्यूड पेंटिंग देख कर असहज हो गईं । थोड़ी देर बाद जब वह पंडित नेहरु से मिलीं तो उन्हों ने सकुचाते हुए , मथाई की शिकायत करते हुए बताया कि यह तो आज मुझे न्यूड पेंटिंग दिखा रहे थे । यह सुन कर नेहरु मुस्कुरा कर रह गए । नेहरु ने साथ उपस्थित मथाई से इस बाबत एक शब्द भी नहीं कहा । एक समय धर्मयुग में लिखे अपने एक लेख में तारकेश्वरी सिनहा ने यह विवरण विस्तार से दर्ज करते हुए यह भी दर्ज किया है कि मथाई ने नेहरु की ब्रीफिंग के मुताबिक ही उन्हें न्यूड पेंटिंग दिखाने की हिमाकत की थी । यह न्यूड पेंटिंग दरअसल थर्मामीटर था , जिस से नेहरु तारकेश्वरी का मिजाज और खुलापन नाप कर अपने करीब लाने के लिए आजमा रहे थे । तारकेश्वरी ने उस लेख में तो यह बात नहीं दर्ज की है पर समय की दीवार पर यह बात दर्ज है कि वह नेहरु की करीबी बन गई थीं । दिलचस्प यह भी है कि तारकेश्वरी ने यह बात धर्मयुग में छपे लेख में तब लिखी जब नेहरु नहीं रहे थे ।

पंडित नेहरु के समय जब वह पहली बार सांसद चुन कर आईं तो एक दिन नेहरु के पी ए मथाई ने उन को फोन कर बताया कि पंडित जी आप से मिलना चाहते हैं । तारकेश्वरी बहुत खुश हुईं । तय समय पर वह पहुंचीं भी पंडित नेहरु से मिलने । लेकिन मथाई ने बहुत देर तक अपने पास ही बिठाए रखा और इधर-उधर की बातें करते रहे । मथाई की बातों से ऊब कर तारकेश्वरी ने पूछा कि आखिर कब मिलेंगे पंडित जी । मथाई ने बताया जल्दी ही । फिर कहा कि आइए तब तक आप को कुछ पेंटिंग दिखाते हैं। पेंटिंग रुम में जब मथाई के साथ वह पहुंचीं तो वहां बहुत सारी न्यूड पेंटिंग भी दीवार पर उपस्थित थीं , जिन्हें मथाई उन्हें दिखाने लगे । तारकेश्वरी सिनहा सहसा न्यूड पेंटिंग देख कर असहज हो गईं । थोड़ी देर बाद जब वह पंडित नेहरु से मिलीं तो उन्हों ने सकुचाते हुए , मथाई की शिकायत करते हुए बताया कि यह तो आज मुझे न्यूड पेंटिंग दिखा रहे थे । यह सुन कर नेहरु मुस्कुरा कर रह गए । नेहरु ने साथ उपस्थित मथाई से इस बाबत एक शब्द भी नहीं कहा । एक समय धर्मयुग में लिखे अपने एक लेख में तारकेश्वरी सिनहा ने यह विवरण विस्तार से दर्ज करते हुए यह भी दर्ज किया है कि मथाई ने नेहरु की ब्रीफिंग के मुताबिक ही उन्हें न्यूड पेंटिंग दिखाने की हिमाकत की थी । यह न्यूड पेंटिंग दरअसल थर्मामीटर था , जिस से नेहरु तारकेश्वरी का मिजाज और खुलापन नाप कर अपने करीब लाने के लिए आजमा रहे थे । तारकेश्वरी ने उस लेख में तो यह बात नहीं दर्ज की है पर समय की दीवार पर यह बात दर्ज है कि वह नेहरु की करीबी बन गई थीं । दिलचस्प यह भी है कि तारकेश्वरी ने यह बात धर्मयुग में छपे लेख में तब लिखी जब नेहरु नहीं रहे थे ।

text:
today is #mentalhealthawarenessday and #mentalhealthawarenessweek .
.
.
you may be thinking "what has this image got to do with mental health", well let me tell you! .
.
.
i was diagnosed with complex ptsd  after things that happened when i was 14 to 15 years old in school.. nhs told me there was no cure, no one qualified to help and a good chance i wouldn't make it to 30.. i was put on around 18 tablets tablets a day and i reached around 26 tablets a day when i was 21 years old, this made things worse and i was no longer me, just an angry zombie..., i was put on countless talking therapies none of this helped
.

then one day, i decided enough was enough i was going to save myself, i came off all 26 tablets a day cold turkey (do not recommend) turned my back on mainstream medicine, and flew to india to learn holistic psychology!  thankfully my parents already were qualified and own @crystalmoonemporium so know all things holistic so they helped me a lot
.
.
.
i felt better, but still felt the c-ptsd was in control not me
.
.
.
i then found out about ayahuasca, i heard how people with the same condition as me had found a way to control it
.
.
.

i flew to mallorca in july to sit with ayahuasca and that is when my life started to change, for good and what i thought at the time bad as i was in tune with every living thing (including plants and animals)
.
.
.
i went back to mallorca last week for a woman's healing retreat and by gosh did i heal!! the c-ptsd will always be with me, but it is my tool now, i control it!! so yes, a yurt does await, your own personal key to unlock the way to healing, just like ayahuasca did for me <3 .
.
.
i wish one day to live in a world that proactively teaches mental health and tries its best to heal rather than try to make money from it and belittle it!!
.
.
.
.
.

#mystory #life #india #mallorca #ptsd #ayahuasca #healing #healed #mentalhealth #mentalhealthwarrior #mentalhealthawareness #dontbescared #love #lovealways #lovevibes #key #journey #yurt #plant #medicine #plantmedicine #share #storytime #myjourney #travel #learn #warrior #metoo

text:
"ännu en insikt om #metoo: vi måste fatta att vi alla har minst en roll i soppan.

vi är offer, förövare eller personer som länge valt att inte se, eller rent av ursäkta, det som händer.

problemet är att den här insikten tenderar förlama folk av skuld, men jag tror vi behöver skilja mellan skuld och ansvar.

kan vi tänka oss att ansvar är något annat, något produktivt?

att se och ingripa när din kompis beter sig som ett svin. lyssna om någon annan påpekar att du beter dig som ett svin. söka hjälp om du inte vet hur du ska förändra ditt beteende." läs ylva pereras essä via länken i bion. 
följ #metoo kvällen i #ylevega #ylearenan @svenskayle 
#dammenbrister

text: 15 oktober 2017 vs 15 oktober 2018. samma dag som startskottet för #metoo-rörelsen bestämde sig vänstra sidan av mitt ansikte att meddela mig att det var dags att lyssna på en kropp starkt anfrätt av stress. fiffigt ändå, det här med att min kropp vet att jag bara lyssnar på tydlig kommunikation 🙃 ansiktet är återställt, kroppen är under behandling - men bäst av allt den rörelse som startade för ett år sedan nu ger effekt; juridiskt, moraliskt, samhälleligt. det är värt allt 💖

text:
when i was a freshman in highschool a guy was annoyed by me so he humped me and grinded himself on my side when i was talking to my friends. i felt disgusted and shocked, it was like a barrier i had kept around myself for safety had been broken. like i was being touched not in that specific area of the body but all around me. like worms had crawled everywhere. 
so i roughly pushed him off me until he fell to the ground. sometimes i wish i beat him up instead but i was too much in a state of shock to do so.i told my teachers and parents but all they did was laugh and dismiss me.
"you shouldve liked it, you're gay right?"
"i mean...he did so many things for you so i guess you can excuse that small mistake right?"
it was one of the first times i was sexually assaulted.

text:
i honestly don't understand the people of this world. they say that they support women, they say that if and when a women is sexually harassed or raped or has gone through something of that sort then they should come forward and talk about it, to create awareness and to change. yet when they get what they ask for and women are now finding the courage to step forward, they are being accused of their allegations being fake and they're not being believed. why do people ask for change if they can't support it when it's happening. the saddest thing for me is that they're so many women who have come forward but because the people being accused are in a higher position of power/fame/or have money, people automatically stay quiet and don't support them. imagine how many more women have been sexually abused by people of power but it's been kept hidden because of their social status and fame. and automatically because this person is well known people are like 'oh he would never do something like that' etc... but how do you know. it's so easy to put forward a fake persona or act a certain way on camera, it's not hard at all. so many people take advantage of their position whether it's someone who is in a high place of authority lawfully, someone who has a higher place in society because they appear to be more religious or pious, or someone who has money and is famous. it's easy for these people to do something like this and get away with it because they know they can brush it under the rug and if it does come out their status in society or in the world will sway people towards them rather then against them. the last thing i have to say is... when someone say's they've been raped or sexually abused/assaulted you should believe them. it takes a lot of courage and bravery to come out about something so traumatizing so do not call that person a liar, let them have their justice, if we really want change in the world and we want to get rid of people who rape and abuse and we want a better world for our brothers and sisters and children then we have to do something about it, speak about it..... @2ukhts || @herfatalmuse

text: (part 2) it’s an unspoken truth, if you are a fit, disciplined, regular gym goer with a good sense of fitness knowledge, you are probably not the most ideal profitable member profile for a gym with a commercial focus, as you may not take most of their key revenue generating services like personal training, etc. but you will be attending the gym almost everyday which relatively increases users on the gym floor at a given time , as compared to an over weight member who is not regular, has no idea about fitness & nutrition would be an ideal member profile giving high revenues & low daily maintenance cost. i have one important thumb rule for everyone to guide you to make the right decision while choosing a gym or a fitness alternative, get fitness literate! educate yourself about your own health, speak to other reliable trainers you know. don’t you find it strange if you are a banker, marketeer, researcher, etc. an ace in your profession but you don’t have enough knowledge about your own body, health, food, fitness requirements? once you have enough knowledge, check around for gyms, fitness studios that don’t aggressively try to promote personal training, other services, but give sufficient attention to training all their members. i hear a lot of folks saying oh we have a gym in the office or i’m a gym member in 2 clubs or i know everything about fitness & health. fitness has to be visible! if you don’t see noticeable results in your health, stamina, overall fitness inside out, over a consistent period of time you may have all the amenities & insights but none of these are benefiting you, it’s just a superficial feel good factor & a waste of your hard earned money! #metoo ! 💪🏻😊👊🏻 #strengthtraining #weighttraining #fitnessmotivation #fitnessmodel @pumaindia #pumahybrid #calvinklein #burberry #porsche #zara #beastmode #fit #crossfit #healthyeating #fitnessgirl #fitgirlsguide

text: 071018 part1. let me tell you something i have kept quiet about for more than four years that finally reached an end. i left home on october 7 on a sunday afternoon after i asked my husband to give me some money to buy food because he hasnt bought food for the past 2 months. he wanted me to pay for my own food. mind you, my husband and soon to be ex husband had always been hostile. i got into healthy food and workout because i wanted to prove myself and god that it is possible to change by giving a person so much love. last week was the final blow. as we were arguing i told him im leaving that day if he doesnt buy food. i explained that i am losing my milk because of stress from our fights & not being able to eat if the neighbor's mom doesnt give me food. he was defiant. so i told him i am taking sofia with me. he grabbed the baby and i grabbed her back. he said "i will call the police if you leave with her". i said go ahead! he gave her to me and i went upstairs. i put sofia on the bed and took my large stroller bag. i entered sofia's room & told his mom who's now using my baby's room: "excuse me i have to take your luggage out 'cause im taking my stuff". the arrogant old woman looked at me and said "are you talking to me?" with her sarcastic face. i said yes, im taking my stuff so im taking out your bag first. she smirked at me! i took my luggage in front of my room and his mom pretended not to know what was happening asked me what happened in a very sarcastic manner. i told her what happened because im stupid thinking she was sympathizing with me. then the old woman said "i dont believe you!" and "altha, i'm not scared of the police. my grandfather was a police officer so you cant scare me". i said sure im not either. and im not the one who said i will call the police its your son! im leaving with sofia today because he doesnt want to buy food. the evil woman said: "you know you cant do that, you cant take her with you" with her very evil face. i said of course i can. she was saying many things as i locked the door. i called cps and the police. i didnt know that time that my husband left the house. his mother stayed behind... to be continued...

text:
да ты страшная и не замужем!
⠀
универсальный аргумент в любом споре с женщиной.
⠀
а если женщина "страшная", не замужем и без детей, значит её борьба за правду и справедливость всего лишь вода.
⠀
то есть вот такая стереотипная связь: лезет на рожон, значит несчастная. и людям даже в голову не идёт, что счастливая в браке женщина с приемлимыми внешними данными тоже может замечать несправедливость.
⠀
внешними данными можно оправдать или обесценить любую неудачу и любой успех. ты можешь быть кем угодно, но если у тебя лишний вес или плохая кожа, то они и говорят за тебя. страшная и всё тут.
⠀
вообще любую деятельность привязывают к внешнему виду и семейному статусу. общество не терпит тех, кто выбивается из установленных схем, чья хата не с краю. кому больше всех надо.
⠀
смотрю я на себя в зеркало и думаю, достаточно ли я одинокая и страшная для феминистки?

text:
we all recognise the importance of continuing to strive towards equality in the workplace. however, there is still a long way to go. in light of the frightening information being shared through campaigns such as #metoo and #timesup we need to give serious consideration to how we better support the safety, wellbeing and growth of women in all workplaces.

created in response to feedback from thousands of female leaders, accord provides a simple, cost effective way for organisations to increase trust and engagement, create connections across various levels and provide a structured environment to nurture and develop female talent. importantly, accord represents an agreement between organisations and their female staff to work together to create a safer, more supportive and more equitable working environment.​ expressions of interest for the accord program are now open- we highly recommend you check it out if you value your female staff members. https://www.wla.edu.au/accord.html #femaleempowerment #womenandwork #womeninbusiness #womenleaders #femaleleaders #safeworkplaces #supportwomen #valuewomen #womenandleadershipaustralia

text:
it was one year ago today the revolution we’ve been working for finally started. women started speaking about the years of harassment, sexual violence and fear. millions of women. millions of stories and experiences. we broke the culture of silence. a culture of keeping it quiet because we could loose our job, reputation, relationships and social status. we’ve kept quiet because we’ve been taught to blame ourselves. because of the fear of more violence. and the fear of not being believed. but no more. you’ll never have the convenience of our silence again.

and it all started with one woman: tarana burke. she started the movement #metoo and one year ago alyssa milano released the wildfire with her tweet about the sexual violence she experienced. women came together from all over the world to demand an end to the war of mens violence against women. the war that have been going on for centuries, in all levels of society, all around the world. women’s bodies are being butchered, just because we are women. we are raped by our colleagues and classmates. we are murdered by the people we love. we are oppressed, humiliated, over-sexualized and attacked in our everyday life. but no more. you’ll never be able to hide behind fake excuses saying you didn’t know.
.
we know that you know now. so every leader, politician, boss, company, school or organization that doesn’t take action to prevent inequality and sexual harassment takes a stand against women. because you know better. so do you want to be a part of the solution - or a part of the problem?
.
men who are allies: act! learn more about toxic masculinity, speak with your friends about being a man today, and speak up: women’s right is not a women’s issue! it’s about humans right and that’s everyone’s business. solidarity equals action!
.
women and non-binary: you are not alone. it wasn’t your fault. and i believe you. and we can demand more: equal pay, new laws, education about sexual violence, report to the police, dump a partner that isn’t treating you right, make your school take action against bullies and so on.
.
and remember that we stand together.
we are never backing down.
we will never again be silent.

text:
the sooner women realize they're not alone, the sooner they can begin their healing journey.

my voice matters.
 http://metoomvmt.org . #drfordloveletter | @taranaburke @amandadecadenet @glennondoyle @traceeellisross @americaferrera 
tarana burke, the woman who founded the #metoo movement

how was the #metoo started?

tarana burke originally coined the phrase me too on 'my space' while working at just be inc., a nonprofit company that was founded by her in 2003.
she started a project focusing on the overall well-being of young women of colour.
the life-changing movement began when burke was talking to a girl who revealed that her mother’s boyfriend had been sexually abusing her.
she didn't know what to say, she just said 'me too'.
burke was left searching for the right words to help empathise with the countless women and young girls who have disclosed their experiences to her.
burke has shared the message with survivors everywhere: you’re not alone. this happened to me too.
she was able to create a storm with just 500 twitter followers.
the movement became an internet sensation when actress alyssa milano stumbled upon this phrase and tweeted this.

#metoo

text:
@michelleobama weighed in on #metoo on thursday, saying the world is “dangerous” for women and girls and that “#enoughisenough .” the former first lady made impassioned remarks about the place of women in modern society, saying “enough is enough” and that the #metoo movement will set the spark for future generations of young women to create change and determine their own paths in life.
“i chose to engage because there’s no choice,” @michelleobama44 said. “the world is a, sadly, dangerous place for women and girls, and we see that again and again. young women are tired of it. they’re tired of being undervalued, they’re tired of being disregarded, they’re tired of their voices not being invested in and heard.” change is not a direct path, obama said. but she urged girls to push through resistance and use their education to lift their voices.
“it’s up to the women out there to say, ‘sorry. sorry you feel uncomfortable, but i’m now paving the way for the next generation,’” she said.
.

text:
english below.
en stille, øde - helt øde - løbetur med ellie. i skønhed og natur. tidlig morgen. jeg har ikke mødt en eneste bil eller et menneske i 5 km. det er vidunderligt, der er frit og højt til himlen. alligevel lurer tanken: hvad nu hvis...? der kom en mand gående imod mig? der kom en bil kørende op bag mig? der kom en gruppe gutter kørende i en truck eller ladvogn? hvad nu... hvis de stoppede og tog mig? hvis de rev mig ud på en af de uendelige marker? så ville ingen høre mig. ingen. og mens jeg engang i mellem på løbeturen ryster tanken af mig og insisterer på at leve i tillid og kærlighed og nyde og mærke vinden og solen i ansigtet og farverne omkring mig, strejfer det mig, at sådan lever mænd ikke. den iboende frygt har de ikke. kender de ikke. kan de ikke identificere sig med. og derfor er det også så svært for selv de bedste mænd helt at forstå bevægelsen #metoo... fordi de ganske enkelt ikke lever med ‘hvad nu hvis’’... hverken på øde steder eller i øvrigt. 
dog jog with ellie. in solitude and open nature. beauty is all around me, and for 4 miles i don’t meet a car or a person. i am🙏! and yet a thought keeps crossing my mind: what if? if a car drives up with a man in it? if a man shows up and walks towards me? i could be dragged out info the fields, i could scream - and no one would hear me. and i keep jogging, insisting on trust and love. even the best of men don’t understand this. they don’t have to be alert. and that’s part of the reason why too many good men don’t really get the importance of #metoo. even when they want to and try. #metoo #dogjog #womaninsolitude #outalone #kvindealene #ødetur #deterderaltid #hvadkvinderlevermed #refleksion #reflexion #feminineleadership #lederskabfradinfemininekerne

text:
🙏my daughter forwarded this meassage to me :
as the #metoo movement takes people by storm, i can't help but think of those incredible men in my life - in whose presence i feel safe... i feel secure... i feel protected... i feel loved.
sometimes, we tend to lose sight of what is right...too important, what is happening and i fully support it. and yet, just a small attempt - to remember... #wetoo have met some of the most amazing gentle, tender, beautiful humans in the world... many of who happen to be men!
i dont want the millions of young girls reading #metoo posts only seeing men in one light, fearing if they too will become a #metoo someday. let's talk as much of what is right too! what say? to my driver, to my cook, to my male friends, to my husband, to my father and to many father like figures in my life... irrespective of some in your gender letting you down, i want to tell you, i still believe in you. #metoo  please share this message if you agree - and want the world to know some bad does not negate the good.

we need to get more eyes on the ‘unprotected’ film over at @propublica — you guys have been an awesome community, getting the attention of important activists by taking a few seconds to tag the right people — so, today we ask the #metoo movement if you are willing to stand up for all women, all survivors, everywhere — @metoomvmt @glennondoyle @taranajaneen @americaferrera @traceeellisross — we encourage you to please watch this critically important documentary, it’s 45 minutes long and it tells the story of one of the most dangerous forms of the white savior complex we’ve come across in our work — it tells the story of young girls in liberia who were already vulnerable, put in an even more vulnerable position by the very people who said they were protecting them — an entire board of directors at @morethanmeorg and their founder @katiemeyler allowed these girls to be repeatedly assaulted, re-traumatized and many even contracted hiv because of these assaults — will you all take a moment to tag @metoomvmt and the women who have been fierce advocates for it? we see them as allies and we are asking them to please pay attention to this and help demand justice for these girls..... #timesup #nowhitesaviors #allblacklivesmatter #blacklivesmatter #morethanmefoundation #morethanme #unprotected

text:
#metoo -vuosipäivä 15.10.2018 #instaruno #proosaruno #kasvatus #perinne #menneisyydenpaino *
eivät he voineet tietää, että ei riittäisi. että joku kantaisi vastuuta. että toista ei saa käyttää. kuinka he olisivat voineet tietää? pikkukaupungin kasvatit, jotka näkivät ympärillään vain vastuutonta käyttöä. kuka sen olisi kertonut? äiti, joka peitti mustelmat meikillä? yksinhuoltaja, joka kantoi harteillaan kaiken? mummo, joka ei enää puhunut? ja koska peruskoulun opetussuunnitelmassakaan ei ollut mainintaa aiheesta, vastaukset piti keksiä itse. "pojat on poikia", oli kuultu sanottavan. ja "rakkaudesta se hevonenkin potkii." näillä tiedoilla he sitten suunnistivat. eikä tullut enää mieleenkään, että ei riittäisi. se oli kokeiluissa todettu täysin käyttökelvottomaksi.

text:
årsdagen för #metoo, och jag har läst min första #metoo-bok. eller, jag har såklart läst massor av böcker där mäns maktmissbruk och kvinnoförtryck förekommit, men det här är den första där #metoo nämns uttryckligen. och det blir en del av problemet med romanen. det känns som att den pressats ut för att hamna rätt i tiden. metoo-upproret förklaras skissartat och tafatt. genusteorier slängs in lite halvgenomtänkt. och slutpoängen... ja, ärligt talat vet jag inte. jag har svårt att se denna boks målgrupp. männen är genomgrisiga (jag vill inte bli "inte alla män"-ig här - men de här grabbarna alienerar förmodligen många män som eventuellt läser). kvinnorna tar offerroller och/eller övertoner (och alienerar mig rätt omgående). så de som är kritiska mot metoo får vatten på sin kvarn. vi som ser rörelsens fördelar får inte veta något nytt. de som inte visste var de stod vet inte mer efter att ha läst, utan blir snarare förvirrade av röriga för-och emotsignaler. 
det finns en god tanke någonstans i grunden, det gör det. jag gillar de tre delarnas upplägg, och de tre  kvinnornas uppdelning över åldrar och roller. jag gillar också att männen får ge sin röst här och var.
men allt är så... halvdant. ogjort. jag gillar inte böcker som blir för långa och tjatiga, men här hade mycket behövt utarbetats mer. det känns stressat, ofärdigt.
dessutom har både wennstam och sveland redan skrivit böcker med exakt samma tema - en ny hashtag räcker inte riktigt för att det här bidraget ska stå för sig själv. synd, för frågan var, är och förblir viktig.
#liselotteläser #patriarkatet
