text:
hot news
kangana ranaut tantang karan johar dan shabana azmi, yang bungkam soal gerakan usut tuntas pelecehan seksual, me too 😉

di tengah gerakan #metoo yang sedang berkembang, aktris kangana ranaut telah memberikan tuduhan kepada sutradara film queen, vikas bahl melakukan pelanggaran dan bahkan meluncurkan serangan baru terhadap hrithik roshan. 
bintang film manikarnika: queen of jhansi kini telah memanggil dan menantang pembuat film karan johar karena mempertahankan keheningan atas isu yang sedang membara itu. jatuh pada sutradara film ae dil hai mushkil, kangana mengatakan kepada media dalam sebuah wawancara, “dimana orang-orang seperti karan johar dan shabana azmi ? orang-orang ini juga harus keluar untuk memberikan suara atas gerakan #metoo juga.”. sungguh ganas perkataan kangana. “karan johar memiliki pandangan tentang penampilan tubuh seorang bintang. dia bahkan menulis tweet sepuluh kali tentang itu. bagaimana dengan ini? inilah identitas mereka. ini roti dan mentega mereka. ketika industri film sedang mengalami perubahan yang penting, dimana mereka?”, tambah kangana geram.

aktris film rangoon ini lebih lanjut mengkritik konsep acara yang dipandu karan, koffee with karan, mengatakan, “saya melihat beberapa promo yang telah mereka luncurkan untuk talkshow ini. lagi-lagi pembicaraan sembrono yang sama sedang berlangsung. yang ini tidur dengan yang ini, yang satu dengan yang itu. membuat gadis terlihat seperti boneka barbie, itu tidak harus dilakukan. dan mengapa pria yang mengubah wanita seperti pakaian sedang dimuliakan? apakah ada seorang wanita yang telah dimuliakan seperti itu”. kangana melanjutkan dengan menambahkan, “kita perlu mempromosikan pria yang memproyeksikan menjadi satu pria-wanita. seseorang yang berpura-pura menjadi casanova, kita tidak perlu memuliakan itu. budaya dimana anda berkencan dengan seorang wanita selama 10 tahun dan meninggalkannya seperti mengganti pakaian. saya tidak menghakimi siapa pun, mereka semua teman saya dan mereka cantik”. kangana dikenal karena tidak pernah menepis kata-kata dan selalu... (selengkapnya baca difacebook) 😉

text:
warning : if you are a *pseudo* feminist then don't read further.

dear #metoo
i have a question for you, will you answer me? please?

actually i was just wondering that can males too use this hashtag? and if they'll do then will society believe them too? if they'll come up with their issues without any proof, will they be listened?

i'm asking all these questions because i believe that everyone has a story to tell.
it's not compulsory that shit happens only with one gender. sometimes it can be a boy too.

just imagine a boy posting that he was raped. yes, there will be some people who'll believe him and will help him too but the majority of comments will go like : 1.
2.
3.
..
..
do i seriously need to mention some? hey come on, i know you already got me.

see i'm not against you, i know things start for a good and so did you. many hidden stories came in the picture. many genuine *humans* got justice. but the society in which we live, these things spread like a cancer. people just exaggerate everything. yeah, i agree it's not easy to use these things for publicity but believe me there are obviously some people who do it for the same.

most importantly, girls just keep their point in words, mind me just in words and we as a society believe them, why? because they are girls. this social media can ruin anyone's life/career and that too in a single day. don't you think that a girl can use this against a boy whom she hates, maybe who rejected her. we as a society say no means no, so same goes for the boys too, maybe there can be a boy who said no to a girl and to take revenge she can use you mr. #metoo, can't she?

everyone suffers! and everyone includes all the genders. i'm not disagreeing that girls don't suffer but with that i agree that boys suffer too. if a boy gains enough guts to raise his voice then not even all other boys will support him, agree?

p.s. - it wasn't intended to hurt anyone's feelings and sentiments, i respect you girls but with that i respect boys too or precisely you can say i respect humans.
-------------------------------------------
#metoo #metoomovement
#metoomovement2018
#metooindia #girls #women #feminism #pseudofeminist #males #boys

text:
the #metoo stories while real are disturbing. as a women who is 30 now, i know that every single women has stories of being harassed in some way or the other - the degree, the circumstance is all that varies.
.
but, while the #metoo stories scare me, given that i need to raise my kannama in this ugliness, it also gives me hope.
.
the world that was unsafe for women to go about their daily routine, is now unsafe for men too in a different way - if you think you can pass a comment on a co-worker and get away with it, think again.
.
the hope again is that the way certain people, brands, companies are being penalized is more permanent, than a temporary one. i've heard enough folks tell me that "the ceo is stepping down till the dust settles".
.
if i've to prepare kannama on how to deal and be safe in this ugly world, than have a safer place at the end of all this, what would be the point really? .
on a separate but connected note, i've also noticed mom influencer profiles being attacked, hacked in the last few days - this is harrassment in the new age, isn't it? i'm speaking specifically about @aweekinlife and @hashtagdisha. the digital world that is enabling women to speak up, is also being used to shut them down?
.
i've been very wary of social media myself. i've never shared a picture of my daughter cos of the fear of how that maybe used. i've never shared too many specifics about our life cos i don't want to risk our privacy or worse, safety.
.
i started this profile to chronicle my journey with my daughter, for me to relive these moments when she is older!
.
but, i also happen to have found a lovely community here and have connected with like-minded individuals - @ammatoday, @andhowdoyoudo, @the.quixotic.quaintrelle and many more!
.
i've also found a bunch of fellow parents who inspire me in the way they raise their kids -@mommy_stories, @artventuretales, @littlefingersatwork, @timesofamma and more.
.
and to think they do all this in the fear that maybe attacked if they speak their own mind?
.
here's hoping for a better world where truly my kannama can feel like she is on top of the world, and flying!

text:
idag deltog jag i debatt i p4 gävleborg och fick frågan: vad tänkte du när #metoo startade och rullade igång för ett år sen? jag var förskräckt. så klart inte förvånad över att problemet med sexuella trakasserier är stort. men metoo var en ögonöppnare om att omfattningen var så stor i så många branscher, och att så många kvinnor blivit utsatta i en stark tystnadskultur där den utsatta blir helt ensam.

att många inte vågar berätta och/eller anmäla kan bero på fler saker. känsla av egen skuld, skam och rädslan av att inte bli trodd. likväl som den arbetssituation som många kvinnor befinner sig i med otrygg anställning, ofta särskild visstidsanställning, försvårar en anmälan.
”lösningen” för arbetsgivaren kan vara enkel: den ”obekvämas” anställning förlängs inte. kvinnan får gå vidare till annan arbetsplats. förövaren får jobba kvar.

vi socialdemokrater har arbetat med frågan extra hårt under det här året. vi vill avskaffa särskild visstidsanställning men också stärka rätten till heltid, begränsa delade turer och mycket mera. vi har gett arbetsmiljöverket (av) och diskrimineringsombudsmannen (do) uppdrag: ta fram en digital plattform för arbetsgivare med syfte att ge stöd att förebygga och förhindra sexuella trakasserier. av har också en skrift som är ett steg framåt inom området, do får även uppdrag att genomföra främjande och tillsynsinsatser.

lagstiftningen måste anpassas. vi har genomfört en samtyckeslag, ändrat lagen så att den utsatte får rätt till målsägandebiträde direkt, höjt straffet för grov våldtäkt från 4 till 5 år, kraftigt ökat anslagen till brottsofferjouren och kvinnojourerna mm.

ingen kvinna ska behöva utstå någon form av sexuella trakasserier. vi vill åstadkomma en kultur där attityder förändras i hela samhället och nästa steg måste vara att det handlar om mäns delaktighet och ansvar. vi vill bidra till att skapa en samtyckeskultur och markera att sex som inte sker frivilligt är att betrakta som ett brott. /åsa

#metoo #metooettår

text:
from the archive (aka loft) evidence of my short-lived ‘career’ as a print baron with my mate jon westbrook.
the launch (and only) issue of ‘it?’ magazine, dated september 1996, featured the divine comedy as the cover star. 
the interview was by jon pictures by yours truly.
we were all over that new-fangled interweb, of course. c’mon, it was 1996!
not to mention the little chat we had with the mighty rocket from the crypt.
we even had album reviews!
it appears that we loved the new offerings from the boo radleys and suede. kula shaker not so much.
other top features included the, um, hilarious ‘bazaar’ spoof showbiz news section. 
our big, completely untrue, story was the blossoming romance between liam gallagher and david bowie. 
weirdly, the one about blur’s damon albarn actually came true, sort of.
we also had a very 2018-esque cartoon about cannabis, in 1996!
but, amongst all this ‘90s indie pop frippery, the piece that really jumps out is @corinnasilk speaking out about men who stared and shouted at her in the street.
remember, this was amidst the burgeoning ‘lads mag’ phenomenon and some two decades before #metoo⁠.

it was called the casting couch and way of business . ..u gonna tell it tell it the way it ways. women where not always victims and made bad choices just like men.... also relationships where also more of a business deal than about love....still going on

the view co-host slams #metoo victims in epic rant!

whoopi goldberg dropped a bomb on the #metoo movement during a talk in leeds, england on saturday.

the outspoken the view co-host ranted that women need to admit they used their sexuality to land film roles and awards.

goldberg, 62, said, “now there’s some things my mother always said to me that i knew were true.

photos: the view’s 30 secrets & scandals “it’s like, if some guy said to me we’re gonna have a meeting up in my hotel room… you don’t f***ing go – you don’t go. “and if you do, cop to it. say, ‘that’s right i went up there and had sex with that ugly-ass man so i could get an oscar and a tony.’ “am i talking about myself? no. we have to teach young women better,” she said.

goldberg isn’t afraid to speak her mind. she once startled the viewfans by defending bill cosby —but soon came out against the comedian, saying on air, “all the information that is out there kind of points to guilt….it looks bad, bill.” photos: the 26 #metoo accused: where are they now?

and in her october 13 leeds speech, the ghost oscar winner also blasted men for “coming after” women who had used the #metoo movement to reveal sexual attacks.

goldberg, who has often been a loose cannon on her morning talk show, noted, “apparently american white men are angry… ’cause they’re top of the food chain, they can get anything they f***ing want but it’s not enough – so they’re coming after women. “women are saying, ‘are you kidding me?’ you can’t put this genie back in the bottle’. women are not taking any bulls**t.” https://radaronline-com.cdn.ampproject.org/v/s/radaronline.com/exclusives/2018/10/whoopi-goldberg-says-actresses-used-sex-with-ugly-men-to-win-oscars/amp/?amp_js_v=a2&amp_gsa=1#referrer=https%3a%2f%2fwww.google.com&amp_tf=from%20%251%24s&ampshare=https%3a%2f%2fradaronline.com%2fexclusives%2f2018%2f10%2fwhoopi-goldberg-says-actresses-used-sex-with-ugly-men-to-win-oscars%2f

text:
i stated plenty times before, automation will wipe over 2.5 billions jobs in less than 10 years.  this is why i recommend current students going to college for robotics and mechatronics engineering. most other degrees and careers will be wiped out. it will be like the industrial revolution.

as with any piece of technology, the first models are expensive, but the more saturated it gets the cheaper the price gets. some examples are the television, ipads, smart phones and plenty more. a 4k television used to be $4000+ when it first came out, now you can get a 55" 4k tv for $300 on black friday.

these robots will be expensive when they first come out, but eventually they will become cheaper to purchase than one construction workers salary. what do you think a company is going to do when he can get one for $30,000. gonna say the hell with paying benefits, salaries and lawsuits and buy one robot and deal with the repairs by hiring some robotic engineers to fix it.

@regran_ed from @lex_j_432hz -  ever notice how we are being subjected to robots? slowly but surely, bigger and more intelligent robots are being deployed for us to buy and use.

we are being conditioned to think it is normal to have robots all over the place, at work and in our houses. for example, we have vacuum cleaners that operate on their own while we relax and do nothing. we think nothing is wrong because we are conditioned to accept this new way of society.

as the years go on, slightly more advanced robots will be released for public use until eventually we have actual human-sized robots inside our houses doing all sorts of things  from doing our laundry, making food and washing dishes.
👀
don’t accept this technology. don’t buy it either. take a look at all the small robots that are available for the public to use and do not buy them! they want to condition us. it’s the transhumanism age.

// “#metoo är bara en häxjakt på oskyldiga män" // den 15 oktober 2017 startade vad vi vill kalla en revolution: #metoo. idag ett år senare talas mycket om en backlash, och trots att vi ser att det händer otroligt mycket runtom i sverige och trots att många av oss upplever att tystnadskulturen en gång för alla brutits, så finns det fortfarande mycket många av oss kämpar med varje dag. 
kan vi inte, dagen till ära, gemensamt samla svar på tal mot dessa föreställningar? vilka argument lyfter ni när ni hör citat som de i bilderna? vad brukar ni svara? skriv siffran och ditt svar i kommentarsfältet nedan. skriv långt eller kort, sakligt eller slagkraftigt, så sammanställer vi och publicerar en svar på tal-guide utfifrån era svar!

ni kan även skriva egna saker ni möter som ni har svårt att svara på så hjälps vi alla åt att hitta bra svar - tillsammans - i kommentarsfältet.

syntolkning: formgivna bilder med citaten som listas i kommentarsfältet nedan.

text:
this account was an impulsive thing but i figured it’s time. 
this account is basically my journey to being a healthier person. 
whether it’s on the outside or in the inside, i want to feel healthier in general. 
let me introduce myself if you don’t already know about me. 
my name is cait. i am 21 years old. i am a wife to an amazing husband, david. we got married this year on cinco de mayo #tacolove. i am mostly a stay at home wife. i got diagnosed with bipolar at the age of 17. before then, was 4 years of hardships and pain (both physical and emotional). i started gaining weight at the age of 11 during my 6th grade summer. i gained about 80ish pounds in 10 years. about every year, i seem to gain 5-10lbs. i recently lost 20lbs back in april. i gained all 20 back plus a couple pounds but luckily still fit my 20lbs ago clothes. my dream is to be a youtuber and share my journey. i have started a blog, which you can see the link in my bio. the blog basically talks about some of the struggles and things i have gone through out the years. i have always wanted to be a motivational speaker ever since i was a kid. i am also a #metoo survivor. 
my goal for this is to maybe help someone out whether they’re having a bad day or maybe just need some inspiration.

somethings i have dealt with that i may talk about in a later blog or video are:
self harm
suicide attempts
suicidal thoughts
anxiety/anxiety attacks
panic attacks
sexual assault
self esteem issues
infidelity

thank you for joining me on this journey towards healthier living!

text:
metoo måste prioriteras 
för över tio år sedan grundade tarana burke metoo för att nå kvinnor i underprivilegierade områden som blivit utsatta för mäns våld. en kampanj som fick ny luft under vingarna när skådespelerskan alyssa milano twittrade #metoo och uppmanade andra kvinnor att dela med sig av sina upplevelser av sexuella trakasserier och övergrepp. idag har ett år sedan milanos tweet och hundratusentals kvinnor världen över har gått med i rörelsen, inte minst här i sverige där den vuxit sig starkare än någon annanstans. 
feministiskt initiativ är ett parti sprunget ur kvinnorörelsen och har alltid arbetat för att bekämpa mäns våld mot kvinnor. därför välkomnar vi de förslag på åtgärder som kommit från samordningen för metoo-uppropen och ger de vårt helhjärtade stöd. vi anser att det är av yttersta vikt att förslagen förverkligas och vi kommer fortsätta driva politik och påverkan för att nå det mål vi alltid har arbetat för – en värld fri från våld. 
vi vill inte att det ska ta ytterligare tio år innan något händer. det är viktigare än någonsin att vi fortsätter lyssna på de vittnesmål som finns i metoo, tar tillvara på den kompetens uppropen besitter och att politiker tar sitt ansvar och påbörjar verklig förändring. metoo måste prioriteras. feministiskt initiativ kommer därför dedikera november månad till att särskilt fokusera på just de frågor metoo handlar om. på vilket sätt får du snart se. viktigast är som vanligt att vi gör det tillsammans.

text_retweet:
regram from @feministerna -  metoo måste prioriteras 
för över tio år sedan grundade tarana burke metoo för att nå kvinnor i underprivilegierade områden som blivit utsatta för mäns våld. en kampanj som fick ny luft under vingarna när skådespelerskan alyssa milano twittrade #metoo och uppmanade andra kvinnor att dela med sig av sina upplevelser av sexuella trakasserier och övergrepp. idag har ett år sedan milanos tweet och hundratusentals kvinnor världen över har gått med i rörelsen, inte minst här i sverige där den vuxit sig starkare än någon annanstans. 
feministiskt initiativ är ett parti sprunget ur kvinnorörelsen och har alltid arbetat för att bekämpa mäns våld mot kvinnor. därför välkomnar vi de förslag på åtgärder som kommit från samordningen för metoo-uppropen och ger de vårt helhjärtade stöd. vi anser att det är av yttersta vikt att förslagen förverkligas och vi kommer fortsätta driva politik och påverkan för att nå det mål vi alltid har arbetat för – en värld fri från våld. 
vi vill inte att det ska ta ytterligare tio år innan något händer. det är viktigare än någonsin att vi fortsätter lyssna på de vittnesmål som finns i metoo, tar tillvara på den kompetens uppropen besitter och att politiker tar sitt ansvar och påbörjar verklig förändring. metoo måste prioriteras. feministiskt initiativ kommer därför dedikera november månad till att särskilt fokusera på just de frågor metoo handlar om. på vilket sätt får du snart se. viktigast är som vanligt att vi gör det tillsammans.

text:
idag har det gått ett år sedan #metoo. en rörelse som ledde till att många kvinnor, och även män, delade med sig av sina upplevelser av sexuella övergrepp och trakasserier. ämnen som det tidigare varit tabu att prata om blev plötsligt till en samhällsdiskussion. tystnadskulturen bröts.
.

när en tystnadskultur bryts kommer saker fram i ljuset och fler kan reagera. när man pratar om saker ser man problem och det leder till att man kan skapa förändring. som politiker har man ett ansvar att just komma med förslag som skapar förändring. förslag som skickar en skarp signal om att vi aldrig kommer att acceptera att kvinnor utsätts för kränkningar och brott.
.

under året som gått har vi fått en ny samtyckeslagstiftning på plats. det är bra och viktigt, men det räcker inte. fler förändringar behövs för ett tryggare samhälle. vi kristdemokrater tar vittnesmålen från metoo på allvar och kommer att fortsätta arbeta för: .
▪️nolltolerans mot sexualbrott - skärp straffen.
.
▪️skapa en nätpolis mot näthat och nättrakasserier
.
▪️ärekränkningslagen bör även omfatta spridning av kränkningar på nätet
.
▪️ge skolor stöd för att se och följa upp trakasserier och hot på internet.
.
▪️skärp lagen om kränkande fotografering
.
foto: urban andersson

text_retweet:
#repost @lydiaekeroth with @get_repost
・・・
my heart is broken for each fellow individual who has experienced sexual violence, and was not only forced to relive their trauma these past few weeks, but was also nationally shamed, silenced, discredited, mocked and devalued by the state and its supporters.  i’m deeply saddened and enraged, but not surprised. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀

our stories are powerful and important. if you want to share yours, please do, we will listen and believe you. if you don’t want to share, don’t feel shame or obligation. your autonomy, safety and wellness is priority.  either way know you are valued, respected, loved and credible. if anyone needs an ear i am here to listen❤️ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀

we pledge to never victim blame. we will listen, honor and protect victims.

but there’s also another conversation that has resurfaced here. 
most of us are overdue for taking a long, hard look at the multitude of ways racism and sexism feed off of each other, and the ways that we, as white women, are complicit in each. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀

white women: we have got to do better. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀

white women protect the patriarchy because we’ve believed that proximity = power. and to some extent that’s correct. there are privileges afforded as a reward for upholding the status quo.  but this comes at enormous cost to ourselves, to women everywhere, to black people, poor people, people of color, lgbtq people and every marginalized group. for decades white women have shortsightedly chosen white supremacy over a global, inclusive women’s liberation ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀

white male supremacy seeks endless power and resources for itself with disregard to the needs, rights and demands of everyone else whom they exploit. white supremacy, patriarchy and capitalism are near inextricable bedfellows that represent the core cause of human suffering. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀

white women: the patriarchy will collapse, but it will do so much more quickly if you stop supporting it. white women voted in trump, supported roy moore, and barely disapproved of kavanaugh. this is crazy. divest now. learn to identify internalized misogyny and your own racism, and shut it down. keep read

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀

white women: we have got to do better. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀

white women protect the patriarchy because we’ve believed that proximity = power. and to some extent that’s correct. there are privileges afforded as a reward for upholding the status quo.  but this comes at enormous cost to ourselves, to women everywhere, to black people, poor people, people of color, lgbtq people and every marginalized group. for decades white women have shosightedly chosen white supremacy over a global, inclusive women’s liberation ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀

white male supremacy seeks endless power and resources for itself with disregard to the needs, rights and demands of everyone else whom they exploit. white supremacy, patriarchy and capitalism are near inextricable bedfellows that represent the core cause of human suffering. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀

text:
#metoo - ett år senare

när #metoo lanserades 15 oktober 2018 var det få som kunde ana vilken genomslagskraft rörelsen skulle få. nu ett år senare kan vi konstatera att inget är sig riktigt likt. mycket positivt har hänt, men samtidigt ser vi på konstmuseet i skövde att #metoo idag behövs mer än någonsin.

på konstmuseet i skövde har vi i snart 20 års tid arbetat aktivt med att synliggöra kvinnors erfarenheter, berättelser och historia. på senare år har även andra normkritiska frågeställningar kommit att bredda vårt tänk och genomsyrar idag det mesta vi gör. vår konstsamling, där mer än två tredjedelar av alla verk är gjorda av kvinnliga konstnärer, är helt unik. det märks tydligt i vår basutställning där vi bland annat visar verk av tidiga feministikoner som siri derkert, vera nilsson, anna sjödahl och lena cronqvist sida vid sida med mer samtida genusorienterade och normkritiska konstnärer som saadia hussain, carolina falkholt, conny karlsson lundgren, catti brandelius och annika von hausswolff.

självklart stannar vi inte där, utan fortsätter att både ställa ut och köpa in verk av konstnärer som på olika sätt synliggör och utmanar vår samtids normer och orättvisor. i vår nuvarande utställning the pavilion med snövit hedstierna, tar hen sitt avstamp i ett mångårigt arbete med mer än 250 intervjuer om hur det är att leva som kvinna eller ickebinär i några av världens mest jämställda länder. med dessa vittnesmål bygger snövit hedstierna en värld där besökaren får möta en dystopisk framtidsvision där patriarkatet har gått segrande ur striden. men kanske finns det ett ljus i tunneln, där de berättelser från kvinnor och ickebinära som finns bevarade i hemliga digitala arkiv – paviljonger – i slutändan kanske kan fungera som en utgångspunkt för ett bättre, mer medmänskligt samhälle. 
utställningen pågår t.o.m. 16 december 2018

text:
there was a time when no one listened to her squeal
no one really cared, a stream of acid made here beautiful face peel.

there was a time when they tried to pull her down
when they teased and lusted her in a night gown.

there was a time when her birth was considered a bad omen
in the mother's womb itself her breath was frozen.

there was a time when her lifeless body was found in the drain,
how could she ever express her pain?

a change is brimming up right now
and we are reaping what we all in the past sow.

a shimmer of hope over the coming days
let all those past cultures have to be set ablaze.

text:
an open letter by priya malik ( @priyasometimes )
.
this is to tell you that while it is courageous to speak about your harassment experiences because everyone is listening right now, it is equally courageous to not speak because you are not ready yet, because you are not comfortable talking about it, because you don’t think it is the right time for you; stay brave. because although it requires a lot of gumption to speak up, it requires the exact amount of courage to stay silent simply because you are not ready yet.
.
you may not have a recorded phone call or a series of screenshots or a gmail chat proof or a string of emails and text messages, you may wish to stay anonymous or show your name, you may wish to not talk about it on twitter but talk about it with your friends, but none of this absolves from the fact that you are living with your truth every minute of the day and by god, that takes strength, courage, resilience and a great degree of self awareness.
.
#metoo #metooindia #metoomovement #priyamalik #shethepeople

text:
thanks @chelseaatwell and @blackpaintstudios @unitedadworkers “united adworkers, tonight is your night. the entire advertising community will have your attention.
as you celebrate the great work that has come out of milwaukee this year, please consider your responsibility as a leader to address the condoned culture of sexual harassment and lack of equity and inclusion that we face as an industry.
these things cannot be fixed with an inclusive graphic. they cannot be solved by passing the problems and emotional burden off on your first female president. these are hollow band-aid solutions.
we all have a responsibility to address the issues in our community.
we have to get to the root of the problems by looking within ourselves. it starts with awareness, and creating an environment where people feel comfortable speaking up. it also takes hard work to expand your perspective and create real change.
look around the room tonight and consider your role in the narrative. are you doing everything you can to make it better? the information here is a start.” #metoo #timesup #timesupadvertising #haveherback

text: for the most part, i've stopped wearing a lot of makeup. i went from a full face and spending hundreds of dollars on makeup (i still love playing with it and doing "full face" sometimes) but the last few months have been about growth, learning,  finding who i am and loving myself. i've been wearing very minimal makeup. today i only wore lightly tinted moisturizer mascara and nude eyeshadow. i'm really learning to love who i am. physically and mentally. i still have a long way to go. however i'm a lot further along the path then i was just a few months ago. ❤️❤️❤️❤️ #selflove #mentalhealth #makeup #growth #spiritualawakening #journey #confidence #natural #startfresh #newme #babysteps #metoo

text:
i cant really say this about just one thing because it's subjective.

if i use love as the example, then yeah i know what it's like to learn a really hard lesson.

loving someone so much you lose yourself, and feeling like you'll never have that love again.

and i never did. i now have something so much better. but if i didnt really learn that lesson about what i needed to give up in order to get what i wanted, what i deserved, best believe history would have repeated. i would have had my heart broken all over jext time round.

this lesson is one of many. every single thing that happens to us, is teaching us a lesson.

dont wallow, dont think "why me". think "why" fullstop. what is the lesson here?

the answers are all around us you just need to look.

text: my take on # metoo . the #movement against #sexual #harassment has exploded in india's entertainment and news industries .#sexualassault is unacceptable. i feel it is an awakening and a reminder that we as a society cannot be complacent. we both have feminine n masculine power, shiva n the shakti.  we need feminine power for creation n nurturing. masculine energy  is action oriented, giving and visionary . at some point  in past society started getting dominated by agressive masculine energies and feminine became weaker and victimised. to have harmony masculine and feminine has to be in balance .then only creation is possible. the women who have joined this movement have chosen to come out of the darkness they are like the phoenix that will rise from the ashes of their shame,guilt , suppression and inhibitions . there is a lot of impact on the mental health of the victim. there is a sense of powerlessness feeling guity or dirty depression and anxiety. overcoming sexual assault takes lot of commitment and time.  but once you overcome the negative into positive, your life will change forever. you will be stronger than before and undoubtedly a better version  of your own self.  power is in the now. it is important to free yourself of the #suppressed emotions especially #anger.self compassion , self forgiveness, healings, meditation and internalisation are some of the tools that can be used for healing this #trauma.it helps a lot to have a trained #counsellor .#selfco@passion #meditation #internalisation #healing #forgiveness #power #now #lifecoachpeyush #mentalhealthsupport #depression #anxiety #lifecoachdelhincr #messagefromtheuniverse #tellmewhatyouthink  #sexualharrasmentatwork#anxietyrelief #lifecoachinnoida #changeyourmindset  #awareness #depressionquotes #metoomovement #metoo

text:
another “pink tie” pic to honor “october breast cancer awareness month.” (and to both female and males who experience the disease.) but better yet, why don’t we men also honor women by eliminating the “assholiness” amongst us (please excuse the vulgarity.) i’ve seen too many men using women as lucre to fulfill their own selfishness. how’d you like your daughter or mother treated like that?
if i could, i’d establish another “arthurian roundtable.” but i don’t want to be king; no, i’d rather serve. honestly, i’d rather be lancelot than arthur.
“the greatest among you shall be your servant.” (matthew 23:11) 
guys, we were not given our strength to dominate, but to defend. let’s be knights. let’s be what men were supposed to be.

text: אתמול בלילה דקות לאחר שנודע על אשה נוספת שנרצחה בידי בעלה, סימסה לי אחות-נפשי יעל אבקסיס: "ענתי זוהי שעת מלחמה". מכאן התגלגל מהלך אליו גייסתי את המומחית לטיפול בנשים נפגעות אלימות רונית לב-ארי וביחד החלטנו על "אזעקת אמת" - ביום חמישי ב-11 בבוקר כל אשה באשר היא מפסיקה את כל מה שהיא עושה לשעה של הזדהות וחשיבה משותפת. מי שיכולה מוזמנת גם להגיע לאספה שנקיים (גם גברים שוחרי שלום מוזמנים) למען מלחמה על החיים, אשה למען אחותה. כי ככה אי אפשר להמשיך. כל המידע בלינק בתגובה הראשונה ותודה לעורך ידיעות אחרונות נטע לבנה שמיד הבין את חשיבות המהלך והעניק לו חשיפה בשער העיתון. קראו את דבריה של יעל - זוהי שעת מלחמה. קראו את מה שרונית אומרת - הנרצחת הבאה כבר בדרך. במהלך היום נמשיך להתגבש ולנסח את הדרישות שלנו וגם נחשוב למי להפנות אותן. בינתיים - חמישי, 11 בבוקר, שעת מלחמה. נפגשים בכיכר דיזנגוף בתל-אביב לחשיבה משותפת. #נשיםמצילותנשים #שעתמלחמה #metoo #להציל_את_הבאה_בתור

text:
on a *new new new* project for me! i've been working (really hard) on my first proper menu consulting for @cafekothi in jaipur. whaaaa. it's been hard to contain my excitement because i've always wanted to try this, and cafe kothi is exactly my vibe ~ fresh, local, seasonal with a focus on health too. foods and flavours are one of my favourite things, and i spend half my time dreaming about them and wanting to try new ideas. so yeah, i'm pretty thrilled with this opportunity to explore everything that it entails - trials and tweaks, tastings and changes, plating, colours, flavours, gosh. (plus, pretty ceramics).
.
we're working on the new winter menu for cafe kothi. i've never worked in a kitchen before, so it's been so much learning every.single.day. kitchens are fairly exhausting work too (props to all of you who do it each day). we're doing dessert today, and i couldn't have asked for a better monday. trying a chocolate-tahini tart. (i've been pretty obsessed with tahini - it works really well in cocoa-date bliss balls, so i can't wait to try this tart). 🤞🏽
.
eeks, so much love @inses and @abhishekhonawar. thanks for the vote of confidence and letting me work on this with you. 🤸🏻‍♀️ (photo ~ @hetalchhabria ♥️).
.
oh, wearing @generationmixx. this new #genderequal tee is the softest, most comfortable. plus, i love the colours.
.
p.s. ~ completely unrelated, but while it's important to keep up with #metoo and have all those conversations to inform your opinions and decisions, it can be emotionally exhausting. plus we've all got to work, be productive and participate in our regular lives. it's completely okay to take a break from it, and go back when you're ready. i took a few days off last week, where i didn't check twitter and it was good for me. #hugs
.
.
.
#menuconsulting #newprojects #28kothi #jaipur #saladsandsmoothies #desserttoo #yay

text:
just another day in the city.
-- today, someone told me that #metoo is getting out of hand. 
it made me realize how oblivious the world is to the struggles of half the population.

so, in sharing as many of our stories as i can on one platform, i'm hoping people see that these aren't isolated incidents. this is the reality for 50% of us!

do send in your stories - anonymously or otherwise - the world needs to know.

text:
there is an essential difference between powerlessness and weaknesses. so when i asked my friend what image does your brain present when we utter the word weak, the reply came: all the women who tolerate abuse from their partners to protect their children. they are perceived as weak and incapable, but they are true survivors.

to all the women out there who lack financial/social means and support to walk out of an abusive relationship and are tolerating it just because of your children. you are not weak! you are a strong human. 
and to all the women who came out of abusive relationships without knowing where the next meal will come from or where you will go for shelter, you are courageous.

#inkrober2018 prompt #weak

text:
last month cristiano ronaldo was accused of rape. this is not the first time this has happened to the juventus striker and one of the most successful, popular and richest athletes in the world. kathryn mayorga filed a civil lawsuit at a nevada district court accusing cristiano ronaldo of rape back in 2009. she eventually dropped these charges after she was paid 375,000 dollars to be quiet nine years ago because she did not want her name to become public. ronaldo along with other big time soccer players like neymar and messi are occasionally in trouble with the law over tax evasion, so they are not new to having issues with the law. this accusation of ronaldo by mayorga has been brushed under the rug because of how big of an athlete ronaldo is. he paid her to be quiet and said this was fake news. this story is still forming and mayorga has filed a lawsuit saying that ronaldo had no right to make this information public. this story is just one example of corruption in major sports and how the victim can sometimes be the one who looks like the enemy. #ecstorytellers #ronaldo #juventus #soccer #sexualassualt #equality #metoo

with conquering limbs astride from land to land;
here at our sea-washed, sunset gates shall stand
a mighty woman with a torch, whose flame
is the imprisoned lightning, and her name
mother of exiles. from her beacon-hand
glows world-wide welcome; her mild eyes command
the air-bridged harbor that twin cities frame.
"keep, ancient lands, your storied pomp!" cries she
with silent lips. "give me your tired, your poor,
your huddled masses yearning to breathe free,
the wretched refuse of your teeming shore.

text:
when i am fortunate enough to interact with people who validate my trauma, which is many of you, i am often told how strong i am. while it gives me some sense of hope, i can't help but feel deceitful because i have been barely keeping it together. but yet, i often preach about empowerment and being kind to yourself.
there are lies we have to tell because we need to believe them ourselves. 
i get asked lots of questions by people who are wondering if it ever gets better and i say "of course it gets better." how could i bear to tell them that i don't know the answers and the limits of their pain? 
my honest answer to you all when you ask if it gets better over time is:
i have had to convince myself of the time and distance between then and now so many thousands of times that surely it has done something, right? or that it gets better until it doesn't. it gets better until there's a split moment where you see someone who looks like him and a sharp pang runs through the center of my body. i feel sick to my stomach. and i have to remind myself over and over that he can't hurt me anymore.
when i close my eyes i only sometimes see his cold eyes staring back, yes, that's an improvements. 
sometimes the reality after it getting better over time is not what you are hoping for. you have to relish the small returns to independence. the nights without the nightmares. the days without the stomach churning anxiety. the panic attack that you got under control. the fact that you only cried once today. it's all been small victories for me. 
that's the truth.

text: my two favorite girls and i went to the square during the me too rally and hung out for a bit, then bailed. desi was a very good girl, but it was too much for me, so i was very glad to see my therapist a few days later. we don’t get to choose how our body responds to trauma, but we do get to choose how we reprocess and deal with the effects of trauma. i haven’t been focusing on fitness or weight loss- just on surviving, and my mental health. yes, i’ve gained weight. yes, i’ve been falling back on unhealthy coping skills by eating all my feelings. but as my dad would ask when i was a kid, “did you do your best?” yep. right now, i’m doing my best. just trying to make one good choice after another. 🖤

text:
fact: the distribution of powers is skewed in the favour of the patriarch. 
musing: the conversation for too long has been about bringing attention to basic rights, but it’s also important to remind ourselves of the beauty in a coven of women. through this collection, i wanted to bring into focus to the solidarity that gets created in the face of resistance.

i felt female when my grandmother taught me how to make mango pickle while reciting monsoon hymns. i felt female when my mother showed me how to drape a saaree. i felt female when my sister told me someone she knew violated her. i felt it when my aunt told me that empowered women are feared. .

#maharani is about touching base with femininity, whatever that might mean for you. it’s about looking at the archetype of the female, rejecting what didn’t work and retaining what did. #metoo

text:
attachment is fear in disguise. let it go. and stop hoarding. stop worrying about things. it’s gonna be ok. love you.

the obsessive need to collect and keep material objects may serve as a coping mechanism for grief, loss or posttraumatic stress.

accumulating “stuff” fills the emotional hole left by the trauma and allows individuals to avoid dealing with the pain. later removal of these items can trigger high levels of anxiety, especially if someone else gets rid of these items without the hoarder’s permission.

text:
hillary clinton vehemently denied in an interview sunday that her husband’s extramarital affair with then-white house intern monica lewinsky was an abuse of power and added that former president bill clinton was right not to resign amid a scandal that led to his impeachment on perjury and obstruction charges.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
“absolutely not,” the former first lady said during the cbs "sunday morning" interview when asked if bill clinton should have stepped down.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
“it wasn't an abuse of power?” cbs news correspondent tony dokoupil asked.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
clinton responded: “no. no.” ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
hillary clinton, who went on to be elected to the senate and served as president obama’s secretary of state, said the relationship was not an abuse of power because lewinsky “was an adult.” at the time of the affair, lewinsky was 22. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
on the defensive, clinton ultimately brought the topic of conversation to president trump and allegations made against him. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣

sur la photo, myriam pageau, maître de cérémonie, essuie ses larmes après un témoignage particulièrement éprouvant.

text:
as a survivor of sexual abuse at the age of 5 and rape at 14, i would like to salute all those that have spoken up and plan on doing so. i know it is very difficult to do it because i have been there and it took me many years to be able to talk about it. it takes immense amount of courage to share this with the world. it’s even harder when you tell those that are close to you and they are supposed to protect you, yet they do nothing. i have been there too and it hurts like hell. but i want these survivors to know it is truly liberating and completely worth it. do not let the nonbelievers stop you. this is your truth. do not ever be afraid to speak your truth. do not let this opportunity pass you. this is a moment that has been long overdue for all of us. this is your chance to be heard and finally obtain justice. i believe you.
.
.
.
.
#metoo #ibelieveyou #somyali #speakup #shoutitout #iamwithyou #survivors #truth #takeastand #staystrong #wecandoit #justice #longoverdue #pakistan #india #bollywood

text: i started @rsvp_lu in 2012 out of desperation. i was in college and really lacking community. i didn’t quite seem to find my clique.. i wondered how many other girls on campus were looking for a community where they could be totally understood and love jesus without this picture perfect model of what that looks like... fast forward to 2018 r.s.v.p.inc. almost 7 years later  is still a thriving female based organization  at lincoln university... it has expanded into a classroom curriculum for “at risk” teen girls in the philadelphia area..and just this weekend we expanded r.s.v.p. past schools  we took the chance and went into the community and started the nyc chapter.  i would love to tell you i had this incredible vision for r.s.v.p. inc.  really i just was a girl that wanted friends and a comfortable place to belong.  some times the longings of your own heart will connect you to the heart of others and just might connect you to your destiny.  here is also the truth: with all the new ways r.s.v.p. is taking off i still have some questions 😅. how will we pay for it?  will people come?  will it be sustainable outside of the school?  but we went afraid, unsure,but totally dependent on god. sometimes you gatta go just with faith. check these pics out from our first nyc event! 👉🏾 #90’spaintandsip.  #sincerelyshanay

text:
one of the emotionally painful situations for me with meeting new people or even people that i know is that people don't listen.

i went to a writers group the other day and it was just myself and this other woman and the teacher and the woman asked me a question about myself. -------------------------------------------------------------------
i answered her & there was somebody coming out of an office and she got distracted and started looking there and didn't hear my answer. ----------------------------------------------------------------------------i asked her, "did you hear my answer?" and she said no and i just said, "that's good to know." --------------------------------------------------------------------------- i can't control other people....but it's very painful for me that people in this society at least a certain amount of people.....not all, don't listen to another person, don't hear the other person..... are not aware. --------------------------------------------------------------------there is such a lack of awareness in the society. it's does happen lot of times, makes it really hard for me to bond with other people as an introvert. --------------------------------------------------------------------------
i have decided to really take care of myself and be willing to remove myself from these situations where people don't listen or hear me. my challenge is, how to keep my heart open despite this. ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- 💕💚💙💗💓💕💙💚💛💛💛💚💙😘💕💓💕💓 #femalestandupcomics #losangeles #haynes_charli #california #standupcomics #charlihaynesnotyourtypicalanorexicskinnybitchyoutube  #oregon #laughteryoga #laughter #losangeles #overcominganxiety #santamonica #hilarious #california #losangelesstandupcomics #spiritual #spirituality #spiritualcomedy #humor #spirituality #metoo #metoomovement #feminism #selfcare #feminismforeverybody #femaleempowerment #funny #peacefulmindpeacefullife #peaceful

text:
even though it sounds extreme, i'm willing to walk away from situations with people that don't listen to me and don't hear me.self care.

the you that’s had a rough week. the you that seems to be under constant storm clouds. the you that feels invisible. the you that doesn’t know how much longer you can hold on. the you that has lost faith. the you thst always blames yourself for everything that goes wrong. to you. 
you are incredible. you make this world a little bit more wonderful. you have so much potential and so many things left to do. you have time. better things are coming your way, so please hang in there. you can do it. just #bebetterthanyesterday 💪🏻

text:
i lied and said i was busy. 
i was busy;
but not in a way most people understand.
i was busy taking deeper breaths. i was busy silencing irrational thoughts. i was busy telling myself i am okay. 
but finally after so long i am physically, mentally and emotionally ready to enter a new phase in my life. i’m ready to grow, get better and #bebetterthanyesterday

write down your goals; long term, short term or  daily. record your progress and tick them off as you go. it’s hard to see a change when you’re so close to something. change your perspective. keep looking back at how far you’ve come. if you’re a visual person; photos and drawing journals will be more suited to you. but no matter what you do keep moving forward and #bebetterthanyesterday

text:
isn’t it interesting that in a split moment, things just click in. everything all of a sudden makes sense.
.
i’ve definitely experienced that this past week and right now, honestly i’m in the opposite of it.
.
i’m in the thick of it all.
.
my anxiety has never been this extremely high and it’s insane the lessons i keep learning and what went down just this past weekend.
.
i feel like i’m honestly just recovering from this like...
.
*spiritual awakening* hangover!
.
that’s what i’m really feeling.
.
i feel like i’m still spun out.
.
and i wanted to make sure i’m sharing my experience from where i’m at today.
.
because tomorrow or the next few moments from now it’ll be different. i know this.
.
i know that you know that too, and staying here with this weird upleveling or whatever is going down.
.
it’s not easy!
.
and then there’s clear examples in my life right now of people being on the other side of this.
.
reflecting of what’s to come, the projection forward, the future, the inevitable. however you want to speak to it.
.
a lot of bad shit happened and a lot of good shit happened this past week.
.
big highs and massive lows.
.
i haven’t fully even processed it.
.
yet i made the choice today to give myself a lot of grace and time, and i’m still in it.
.
and it’s really important to show up in all of who we are. always.
.
it’s all so good!
.
and all of it has a spot in our lives.
.
you are never alone.
.
you are safe.
.
you can feel and experience it all.
.
to ultimately have it all, that sometimes is the flip side of it all.
.
📸 @oana_dragan

text:
i’ve struggled with disordered eating for 20 years. 
i always find myself minimizing this because, how can you have an eating disorder and be plus-size. i would roll my eyes when girls said they had anorexia assuming they just wanted attention, so i figured since i wasn’t telling everyone about it then it wasn’t a problem. 
but the thing is, i wear that problem every single day. you can literally see my disorder. i remember as a teenager being told how my voracious appetite for candy would catch up to me one day. i vividly remember eating 3 candy bars everyday during drivers ed. if that’s not disordered, idk what is. 
it’s taken me a long time to come to terms with it. i have to tell myself everyday, sometimes every hour, that i do like being healthy!

i actually feel better and have better control over every area in my life when i’m staying on top of my nutrition. but once one plate drops it all goes to hell. and that’s where accountability has to come. 
having someone who i’m checking in with daily, if not multiple times a day has made such a huge difference!! and knowing that there’s someone there that if i fall off the wagon and eat two pounds of cinnamon bears in one day, i can turn to them...it’s priceless. 
and that’s what i’m trying to give out in return. i’ve found an incredible nutrition program that not only allows me to eat and enjoy it but also lose weight at the same time. so i’ve got a simple routine, accountability i can trust, and workouts available when it fits with my schedule 🙌🏼. if you’ve got emotional eating problems, overheating issues, and feel completely lost and don’t know how you can make a change, i’d love to talk more and see if i have a solution for you! 
because babe, you’ve probably tried every program under the sun, but i know this can work for anyone! you are worth the work it takes to dig out, and i promise, it’s way easier than you think! i’m rooting for you!!!

text:
i am not a nice girl. 
i guess this piece is done. i began this project all the way back in february but set it aside for several months when i lost steam. recent weeks have inspired me to finish it. 
if we get angry, we are overbearing bitches. if we cry or scream, we are hysterical or overemotional. our expression of ourselves, our reaction to the world around us and how others treat our bodies is tightly controlled by the expectation to always be "nice, pleasant and accommodating." meanwhile, men's anger is rewarded as "passionate." well, i am not a nice girl and i don't give a fuck about what you think. be mad. be very mad.

text:
the first part of this is pretty clear. the only clarifying it might need is that i don't really think the question is about whether we "believe." rather, i think it is more about whether we care.

the second half comes from being a teacher and a therapist. my stance on the changes that are needed now comes from the fact that i believe men are capable of more. i believe in men, means i believe they can do better. and, i believe it is harmful to them to do harm, and so it is actually a compassion to demand them to stop (it is not a compassion to condone it). believing in men is actually an important counter to the rhetoric that "men are biologically wired [to rape, to look down your shirt, to whatever else....]" and that there is nothing they can do about it. this rhetoric–carried by many women–furthers the belief that men cannot control themselves, are less smart, strong or self-aware than women, and do not have the same capacity for emotions or respect. and i just don't buy it! i think way more highly of them. people who carry this rhetoric often fail to notice that it is the same logic behind blaming the victim. 
the second part of "i believe in men" creates the space for ones who have made a mistake to atone, see the error, and become an ally. i do think it is important that those who have misused power face consequences, have losses and be distanced or restrained in any way needed to keep others safe. but there must also be a path to heal and to create something new. 
don't use the "i believe in men" to go to the good-guy-storyline either. my saying this does not collude with the men who get defensive around the current situation saying "most guys are good." i believe in men also applies to being strong enough to not be defensive. 
let's just add one more thing to this though. maybe for a while, men could listen rather than explain. maybe they could let women take the lead of the healing of their own wounds. men: you are strong enough to stop. you are strong enough to listen. #metoo #therapy #menstherapy #somaticpsychology #psychology #ibelievewomen #healing #emotions #teachers #patriarchy #men #atonement #apologize #repair #humans

text:
president trump says he deserves credit for sealing supreme court justice brett kavanaugh's confirmation by mocking christine blasey ford's testimony before the senate judiciary committee at a campaign rally.⠀
⠀
"had i not made that speech, we would not have won," trump said during an interview with cbs news' "60 minutes" that aired sunday night. "i was just saying she didn't seem to know anything."⠀
⠀
while addressing a crowd in early october in southaven, miss., trump mimicked ford's failure to remember details from the night during the summer of 1982 when she claims kavanaugh groped her and tried to remove her clothes. kavanaugh has denied her accusations.⠀
⠀
⠀
"i had one beer and that's the only thing i remember," trump said at the time, imitating ford's testimony. ⠀
⠀

text: i want to tell anyone that thinks their dreams can’t come true... that is a bunch of bull shit. 10 years ago i was in a bad spot, a really bad spot. i had alienated myself from family who loved me, i was fighting chronic pain from a cycling accident that could have killed me, and had been taken advantage of. i thought i’d never be able to trust or love anyone. running and fitness kept me alive as did hard headed ness and a refusal to give in to those that said i couldn’t succeed. today i have proved them wrong .. i’ve overcome the obstacles to return to running and am in the most loving relationship with my best friend and someone i love more than anything in the world, have parents who love me, and hope i can inspire others to follow their dreams. tough times don’t last but tough people do. never forget that!! #nevergiveup #gratitude #metoo #followyourdreams #courage #determination #runner #running #runstrong #cyclist #overcomingadversity #livelife #fitlife #familyfirst #followyourheart #mindbodysoul #perserverance
